2:41:47','2012-11-12 02:41:47','We\'ll get back to you soon!','Thank You For Your Submission','','inherit','open','open','','64-revision-5','','','2012-11-12 02:41:47','2012-11-12 02:41:47','',64,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/64-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(71,1,'2012-11-12 02:50:46','2012-11-12 02:50:46','Please complete the registration from below and we will contact you via email, or phone, as soon as possible.','Family Registration Form','','publish','open','open','','family-registration','','','2012-12-03 01:30:47','2012-12-03 01:30:47','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=71',0,'page','',0),(72,1,'2012-11-12 02:50:33','2012-11-12 02:50:33','','Family Registration Form','','inherit','open','open','','71-revision','','','2012-11-12 02:50:33','2012-11-12 02:50:33','',71,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/71-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(73,1,'2012-11-23 05:44:53','2012-11-23 05:44:53','Here\'s the family registration form.','Family Registration Form','','inherit','open','open','','71-autosave','','','2012-11-23 05:44:53','2012-11-23 05:44:53','',71,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/71-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(82,1,'2012-11-16 03:34:04','2012-11-16 03:34:04','something in here.\r\n\r\nmore things!','Jones/Gerrard','','publish','closed','closed','','jones-gerrard','','','2012-11-20 02:32:06','2012-11-20 02:32:06','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?post_type=share_family&#038;p=82',0,'share_family','',0),(83,1,'2012-11-20 02:33:07','2012-11-20 02:33:07','','Jones/Gerrard','','inherit','open','open','','82-autosave','','','2012-11-20 02:33:07','2012-11-20 02:33:07','',82,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/82-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(110,1,'2012-11-19 20:00:25','2012-11-19 20:00:25','','Queen/Jones Family','','publish','closed','closed','','queen-jones','','','2012-11-20 02:31:38','2012-11-20 02:31:38','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?post_type=share_family&#038;p=110',0,'share_family','',0),(111,1,'2012-11-19 23:06:39','2012-11-19 23:06:39','','Queen/Jones Family','','inherit','open','open','','110-autosave','','','2012-11-19 23:06:39','2012-11-19 23:06:39','',110,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/110-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(115,1,'2012-11-19 20:33:59','2012-11-19 20:33:59','Sometimes sharing a nanny might be the best option for your family – a more affordable alternative!\r\n\r\nWhen two families come together to share a nanny for their children, this is called a “Nanny Share”.\r\n\r\n<strong>Option 1:</strong> The nanny can care for both sets of children on all days Monday- Friday. There is usually only 1 child from each family in this option.\r\n<strong>Option 2:</strong> The nanny alternates between caring for one family’s children on one day, and the other family’s children on the other days.\r\n<div class=\"divider div3\"></div>\r\nWith a nanny share, the families involved should have the same philosophies on parenting, routines, discipline, etc. In most nanny shares, the involved families have one child each. Nanny share nannies usually work between 45- 50 hours per week.\r\n\r\nMany families would like to alternate between the two houses, 1-2 weeks in each home. This can unsettle the children and disrupt their routine. Consistency is very important for young children. It can also disrupt the nannies schedule especially when children’s items are left at the other home eg favourite toy, winter hats and gloves, sunscreen, bottles.\r\n<h4>Points to consider when starting a Nanny Share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>The household where the children will be based will need to have an extra sleeping area and bed (pack and play)</li>\r\n	<li>The cost of children’s groceries will need to be halved ie. milk, food, diapers, wipes</li>\r\n	<li>Transport for two children, whether it be two car seats or a double stroller if needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Transporting your child’s bottles every morning and afternoon or buying an extra set for the other house</li>\r\n	<li>For the house that is having the children that there will be more toys, bottles, plates, cups in your home.</li>\r\n	<li>When the nanny gets vacations which would work for both families. Most nannies get between 2 weeks’ vacation and the days between Christmas and New Year. For the two weeks I always recommend that the families pick one week and the nanny picks the other week to make it fair.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Positives of being a part of a Nanny share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Sharing the cost of the nanny ages/ salary</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to socialize with children their own age</li>\r\n	<li>Develop a close friendship with the other child</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to share and participate with each other.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"controls\"><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-sharing\';\">Looking For A Family</button><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-looking\';\">Families With A Nanny To Share</button></div>','Nanny Share Family Finder','','publish','open','open','','nanny-share','','','2012-12-03 02:26:15','2012-12-03 02:26:15','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=115',0,'page','',0),(116,1,'2012-11-19 20:33:41','2012-11-19 20:33:41','Welcome to the new Nanny Share Family Finder. Bumble Bees Nannies knows how difficult it is to find other families to share with. Now you can look here to find families and see what they are looking for.\n\n<strong>How It Works</strong>\n\nTo get your details on the Family Finder, you need to contact Richelle and fill out an application form. The application form will give you guidance on what you are looking for in a nanny.\n\nFrom there, you will get a family number and your basic details will be put online. Your personal details will stay confidential. If a family is interested to get in contact with you, I will only pass out your phone number or email address depending on which one you give permission for.\n\nIf you are interested in a family you see below, please click the box.\n\nOnce you and the other family decide to work together and decide to use Bumble Bees','Nanny Share - Families','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision','','','2012-11-19 20:33:41','2012-11-19 20:33:41','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(117,1,'2012-11-19 20:35:30','2012-11-19 20:35:30','','Nanny Share','','publish','open','open','','nanny-share-3','','','2012-12-06 02:04:54','2012-12-06 02:04:54','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=117',16,'nav_menu_item','',0),(118,1,'2012-11-19 20:33:59','2012-11-19 20:33:59','Welcome to the new Nanny Share Family Finder. Bumble Bees Nannies knows how difficult it is to find other families to share with. Now you can look here to find families and see what they are looking for.\r\n\r\n<strong>How It Works</strong>\r\n\r\nTo get your details on the Family Finder, you need to contact Richelle and fill out an application form. The application form will give you guidance on what you are looking for in a nanny.\r\n\r\nFrom there, you will get a family number and your basic details will be put online. Your personal details will stay confidential. If a family is interested to get in contact with you, I will only pass out your phone number or email address depending on which one you give permission for.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in a family you see below, please click the box.\r\n\r\nOnce you and the other family decide to work together and decide to use Bumble Bees Nannies, then I will use your application forms to look for a nanny for you.','Nanny Share - Families','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-2','','','2012-11-19 20:33:59','2012-11-19 20:33:59','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(119,1,'2012-11-19 20:38:07','2012-11-19 20:38:07','Welcome to the new Nanny Share Family Finder. Bumble Bees Nannies knows how difficult it is to find other families to share with. Now you can look here to find families and see what they are l