alified nannies have so much to offer, helping children have a great start in life. From teaching children as they play, preparing them for school, giving them love and attention, Bumble Bees Nannies will use all their knowledge and experience to fulfill the children\'s needs, providing a healthy, educational and safe environment\"\r\n\r\n- <strong>Richelle Assenberg</strong>, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsing Bumble Bees Nannies will help you find your perfect nanny. Using our agency means that you don\'t have to do all the work which is involved in hiring someone to work with children; answering the many phone calls you will receive of interested caregivers looking for work or responding to all the emails, searching the internet daily, checking resumes and conducting many interviews. This work can take a lot of time up, let Bumble Bees Nannies do this all for you.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is alos registered with Toronto Police so we can conduct Vulnerable Person\'s Police Checks with written permission from the applicants.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is the place to go in Toronto when searching for excellence in childcare services for your family\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4>Positives Of Having A Nanny</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your child will receive more attention from the caregiver - one on one</li>\r\n	<li>Your child will develop a close bond with the nanny quicker than in a daycare</li>\r\n	<li>Your children will be able to go on trips on a regular basis, weekly or bi-weekly; parks, zoo, science centre, swimming</li>\r\n	<li>Consistency and routine of being with another child and nanny builds trust and stability</li>\r\n	<li>You are able to come home and your children have had their dinner and are ready to spend quality time with you. No daycare runs and then having to go home and still cook dinner for your children and get them ready for bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>What Differentiates Us?</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We will guide you through the process in finding the right childcare solution for your family</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies conducts face-to-face meetings with families, getting to know our clients and their childcare needs to facilitate the perfect nanny match</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies recommends have trials that are 2-4 days long to see if the nanny suits your family and to see if they fit in. This reduces the chance of nanny\'s not working out</li>\r\n	<li>3 Month Trials: If your nanny decides to leave, Bumble Bees Nannies will attempt to find a suitable replacement free of charge</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies will provide full support for families throughout the 3 Month Trial</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Customized, personal service</strong> - simply the best for your family!</li>\r\n</ul>','Families','','inherit','open','open','','154-revision-7','','','2012-11-22 05:54:08','2012-11-22 05:54:08','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/154-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(164,1,'2012-11-23 03:18:01','2012-11-23 03:18:01','At Bumble Bees Nannies all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume as well as an Application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years’ experience they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children, why they stopped working with their last employer.   During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies, and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a family.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div4\"></div>\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks: \r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n<li>References</li>\r\n<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\r\n<li>Up-to-date Police check. A vulnerable Persons Police Check will be conducted once a nanny has been offered a job</li>\r\n<li>Driver’s License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\r\n<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nWhile going through their resume/CV we look for any loopholes/ gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\r\n\r\nWith Bumble Bees doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates so let Bumble Bees do all the work,  finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\r\n\r\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process we are confident that we can find the right nanny for your family.','Nanny Screening Process','','publish','open','open','','nanny-screening-process','','','2012-12-02 01:09:07','2012-12-02 01:09:07','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=164',0,'page','',0),(165,1,'2012-11-23 03:17:52','2012-11-23 03:17:52','What is the screening process for nannies joining Bumble Bees Nannies?\n\nAt Bumble Bees Nannies, all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume, as well as an application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years experience, they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children and why they finished with their last employer. During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a  family.\n\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks:\n<ul>\n	<li>References</li>\n	<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\n	<li>Up to date Police Check</li>\n	<li>Drivers License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\n	<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\n</ul>\nWhile going through their resume/CV, we look for any loopholes/gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\n\nWith Bumble Bees Nannies doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount of nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates, so let Bumble Bees Nannies do all the work finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees Nannies aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\n\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees Nannies requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process, we are confident that we can find the r','Nanny Screening Process','','inherit','open','open','','164-revision','','','2012-11-23 03:17:52','2012-11-23 03:17:52','',164,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/164-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(166,1,'2012-11-23 03:19:00','2012-11-23 03:19:00','','Screening Process','','publish','open','open','','166','','','2012-12-06 02:04:53','2012-12-06 02:04:53','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=166',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(167,1,'2012-11-23 03:26:45','2012-11-23 03:26:45','<h4>Nanny Pay Scale</h4>\r\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a <a title=\"Childcare Options\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/childcare-options/#live-out-nannies\">Live-out</a> nanny:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Part-time nannies ( less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12-$20 an hour</li>\r\n	<li>35-40 hour week- between $ 450-550 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n	<li>40-50 hour week- between $500-$650 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny’s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n\r\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\r\n\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nTo pay your nanny you will need to apply for a Business number with The Canadian Revenue Agency. This is a very simple process. Once this has been done you can either use The Canadian revenue agency or use Bumble Bees Nannies’ new Nanny Payroll service. \r\n\r\n<h4>Bumble Bees Nannies Payroll</h4>\r\n<div class=\"payroll-table\">\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is now offering a new service: Nanny Payroll. We will start this service in January 2013. This service will reduce all your worry with paying your nanny.\r\n\r\nFor $300 per year, we\'ll help take care of:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n<li>Calculating your nanny\'s gross net pay</li>\r\n<li>Nanny direct deposit</li>\r\n<li>Pay the CRA remittances on time on your behalf</li>\r\n<li>Issue a T4 at year end</li>\r\n<li>Issue a Record of Employment for your  nanny at the end of employment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','publish','open','open','','nanny-pay-scale-and-tax-information','','','2012-12-02 02:06:15','2012-12-02 02:06:15','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=167',0,'page','',0),(168,1,'2012-11-23 03:26:25','2012-11-23 03:26:25','Nanny Payscale\n\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours. Live-out and Live-in nannies receive a different salary because the living costs (accommodation and food) are taken into account for Live-in nannies.\n\nAn estimated cost of a Live-out nanny:\n\nPart-time nannies (less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12 - $20 an hour.\n\n35-40 hour week - between $450 - $500 per week, net.\n\n40-50 hour week - between $500 - $600 per week, net.\n\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny\'s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\n\n<h4>Tax Information</h\n\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\n\nThis can be done through the Canadian Revenue Agency or with Bumble Bees Nannies.\n\n&nbsp;','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision','','','2012-11-23 03:26:25','2012-11-23 03:26:25','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2012-11-23 03:26:45','2012-11-23 03:26:45','The required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours. Live-out and Live-in nannies receive a different salary because the living costs (accommodation and food) are taken into account for Live-in nannies.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a Live-out nanny:\r\n\r\nPart-time nannies (less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12 - $20 an hour.\r\n\r\n35-40 hour week - between $450 - $500 per week, net.\r\n\r\n40-50 hour week - between $500 - $600 per week, net.\r\n\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny\'s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nThis can be done through the Canadian Revenue Agency or with Bumble Bees Nannies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-2','','','2012-11-23 03:26:45','2012-11-23 03:26:45','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2012-11-23 03:27:22','2012-11-23 03:27:22','','Pay Scale and Tax Information','','publish','open','open','','170','','','2012-12-06 02:04:53','2012-