evision-3','','','2012-11-11 18:05:59','2012-11-11 18:05:59','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(180,1,'2012-11-25 02:34:50','2012-11-25 02:34:50','Contacting Bumble Bees Nannies couldn\'t be any simpler.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:richelle@bbnannies.ca\">richelle@bbnannies.ca</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-4','','','2012-11-25 02:34:50','2012-11-25 02:34:50','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(181,1,'2012-11-25 02:35:10','2012-11-25 02:35:10','Contacting Bumble Bees Nannies couldn\'t be any simpler.\r\n\r\n<strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:richelle@bbnannies.ca\">richelle@bbnannies.ca</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-5','','','2012-11-25 02:35:10','2012-11-25 02:35:10','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2012-11-25 04:17:31','2012-11-25 04:17:31','Contacting Bumble Bees Nannies couldn\'t be any simpler.\r\n\r\n<div id=\"cntr-contact-info\">\r\n<strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:richelle@bbnannies.ca\">richelle@bbnannies.ca</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"cntr-map\"></div>\r\n','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-6','','','2012-11-25 04:17:31','2012-11-25 04:17:31','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(183,1,'2012-11-25 04:21:38','2012-11-25 04:21:38','&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"cntr-contact-info\"><strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1<a href=\"mailto:richelle@bbnannies.ca\">richelle@bbnannies.ca</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"cntr-map\"></div>','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-7','','','2012-11-25 04:21:38','2012-11-25 04:21:38','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(184,1,'2012-11-25 04:21:58','2012-11-25 04:21:58','<div id=\"cntr-contact-info\"><strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1<a href=\"mailto:richelle@bbnannies.ca\">richelle@bbnannies.ca</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904</div>\r\n<div id=\"cntr-map\"></div>','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-8','','','2012-11-25 04:21:58','2012-11-25 04:21:58','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(185,1,'2012-11-25 04:26:25','2012-11-25 04:26:25','<div id=\"cntr-contact-info\"><strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href=\"mailto:richelle@bbnannies.ca\">richelle@bbnannies.ca</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904</div>\r\n<div id=\"cntr-map\"></div>','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-9','','','2012-11-25 04:26:25','2012-11-25 04:26:25','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(187,1,'2012-11-27 03:11:45','2012-11-27 03:11:45','<strong>1. What your family needs from a childcare professional</strong>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Do you need someone to help solely with your children or also run errands?</li>\r\n	<li>Do you need an extra pair of hands around the house to help with the children?</li>\r\n	<li>Does the child care professional need to be active and young at heart?</li>\r\n	<li>How many years experience would you like the nanny to have?</li>\r\n	<li>Is a driver necessary for school runs, after school activities or play dates?</li>\r\n	<li>Full or part time?</li>\r\n	<li>Would both parents be at work during the day so you need a very qualified nanny, with great communication skills?</li>\r\n	<li>Would you like your caregiver to have the same interests as you or your children?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>2. Shall I hire a Live-In or Live-Out Nanny?</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Live-In Nanny</strong>:\r\n\r\nThe salary of a live-in nanny is lower than a live-out nanny because the food and accommodation is taken into account. If the nanny lives with you, you need provide a bedroom, living area, bathroom and theyneed to have access to the kitchen and most areas of the house, they become a part of the family and a close bond with the nanny and family is usually developed quite quickly.\r\n\r\nA negative side to consider is the lack of privacy after hours and in weekends.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately Bumble Bees Nannies does not offer Live-in Nannies.\r\n\r\n<strong>Live-Out Nanny</strong>: Families choose live-out nannies if there is a lack of space for a nanny to live with the family and the family want to keep their privacy, especially in the weekends and after hours. Most of the qualified and experienced nannies are Live-out nannies; they have their own homes, families to go back to at the end of each day.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Contact Bumble Bees Nannies via Email or Phone</strong>\r\n\r\nFill in an <a title=\"Family Registration Form\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/family-registration/\">online form</a> with the basic details of your family needs and then we will contact you with further questions. Or email <a href=\"mailto:richelle@bumblebeesnannies.com\">Bumble Bees Nannies</a> directly with a brief message on what you are looking for and we will contact you as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Application Forms</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce this has been done, we will call you to discuss your needs and answer any questions you may have. An application form will then be emailed to you that you will need to fill out and email back. We use this to write job descriptions for the nannies to read and to help us get a sense of what you are looking for to make the match.\r\n\r\nAt Bumble Bees we like to conduct face to face meetings with families at a local café during the day so we can get a better idea of what the family needs are so we can match you with a nanny. We not only match by family requirements but also by personalities and interests.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Nanny Search</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has received the application form, we will start looking for nannies who suit your needs and wants. During this process, we will keep in regular contact with you, updating you on the progress.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Interview Process</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has found nannies that we think will suit what you are looking for, you will be emailed resumes to read through as well as our own personal thoughts about why the nanny would suit your family. If you are interested in the nannies, an interview will be setup. During this stage, a <a title=\"Fee Structure\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/fee-structure/\">Booking Fee</a> will be invoiced to you.\r\n\r\nOnce you have had your interviews and have decided on a  nanny, a Nanny Trial will be arranged. This is so that the family and nanny get to know each other before a job offer is made.\r\n\r\n<strong>7. Nanny Trials</strong>\r\n\r\nRichelle recommends a trial so that the family can see the nanny interact with the children and family and for the nanny to see how the parents interact with their children. It should be a relaxing time, so the nanny can settle in and feel comfortable. It is recommended that the family pay the nanny for this time, minimum wage and last between 3-4 hours or to 4-5 days, depending on how well you feel it is going.\r\n\r\n<strong>8. Final Steps</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce you have decided on a nanny then we can make a job offer to the nanny. If she accepts then Bumble Bees Nannies will assist you in writing a contract.\r\n\r\nYou will receive a more descriptive ‘Step by Step’ when contacting Bumble Bees Nanny Agency.','Families Step-By-Step','','publish','open','open','','families-step-by-step','','','2012-12-02 01:22:54','2012-12-02 01:22:54','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=187',0,'page','',0),(188,1,'2012-11-27 03:11:40','2012-11-27 03:11:40','<strong>1. What your family needs from a childcare professional</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li> Do you need someone to help solely with your children or also run errands?</li>\n	<li>Do you need an extra pair of hands around the house to help with the children?</li>\n	<li>Does the child care professional need to be active and young at heart?</li>\n	<li>How many years experience would you like the nanny to have?</li>\n	<li>Is a driver necessary for school runs, after school activities or play dates?</li>\n	<li>Full or part time?</li>\n	<li>Would both parents be at work during the day so you need a very qualified nanny, with great communication skills?</li>\n	<li>Would you like your caregiver to have the same interests as you or your children?</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>2. Shall I hire a Live-In or Live-Out Nanny?</strong>\n\n<strong>Live-In Nanny</strong>: The salary of a live-in nanny is lower because the food and accommodation is taken into account and there is extra room to accommodate the nanny (bedroom, living area, bathroom - which can be shared with the children). If a nanny lives with you, they need to have access to the kitchen and most areas of the house, tehy become a part of the family and a close bond with the nanny and family is usually developed quite quickly.\n\nA negative side to consider is the lack of privacy after hours and in weekends. Most nannies keep themselves busy and have a V in their living area, but they do need to share the kitchen and bathrooms with the family.\n\n<strong>Live-Out Nanny</strong>: There is a lack of space for a nanny to live with the family and the family want to keep their privacy, especially in the weekends and after hours. Most of the qualified and experienced nannies are live-out nannies, they have their own homes and families to go back to at the end of each day.\n\n<strong>3. Contact Bumble Bees Nannies via Email or Phone</strong>\n\nFill in an <a title=\"Family Registration Form\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/family-registration/\">online form</a> with the basic details of your family needs and then we will contact you with further questions. Or email <a href=\"mailto:richelle@bumblebeesnannies.com\">Richelle</a> directly with a brief message on what you are looking for.\n\n<strong>4. Application Forms</strong>\n\nOnce this has been done, we will call you to discuss your needs and answer any questions you may have. An application form will t hen be emailed to you that you will need to fill out and email back. We use this to write job descriptions for the nannies to read and to help us get a sense of what you are looking for to make the match.\n\nBumble Bees Nannies likes to conduct face to face meetings with families as well as nannies so they can get a better idea of the family so we can match you with a nanny, not only by interests and family requirements, but also by personalities.\n\n<strong>5. Nanny Search</strong>\n\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has received the application form, she will start looking for nannies who suit your needs and wants. During this process, we will keep in regular contact with you, updating you on the progress.\n\n<strong>6. Interview Process</strong>\n\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has found nannies that we think will suit what you are looking for, you will be emailed resumes to read through as well as our own personal thoughts about why the nanny would suit your family. If you are interested in the nannies, then an interview will be setup. During this stage, a Booking Fee will be invoiced to you.\n\nOnce you have had your interviews and have decided on a  nanny, then a Nanny Trial will be arranged. This is so that the family and nanny get to know each other before a job offer is made.\n\n<strong>7. Nanny Trials</strong>\n\nRichelle recommends a trial so that the family can see the nanny interact with the children and family and for the nanny to see how the parents interact with their children. It should be a relaxing time, so the nanny can settle in and feel comfortable. It is recommended that the family pay the nanny for this time, minimum wage and last between 3-4 hours or to 4-5 days, depending on how well you feel it is going.\n\n<strong>8. Final Steps</strong>\n\nOnce you have decided on a nanny, then we can make a job offer to the nanny. If she accepts, then Bumble Bees Nannies will write a contract for you and the nanny can start.\n\nYou will receive a more descriptive \'Step-by-Step\' when we contact you so you know in detail how it works.','Families Step-By-Step','','inherit','open','open','','187-revision','','','2012-11-27 03:11:40','2012-11-27 03:11:40','',187,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/187-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(189,1,'2012-11-27 03:12:52','2012-11-27 03:12:52','','Step-By-Step','','publish','open','open','','step-by-step','','','2012-12-06 02:04:53','2012-12-06 02:04:53','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=189',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(190,1,'2012-11-27 03:23:37','2012-11-27 03:23:37','Bumble Bees Nannies will email resumes for you to look at without charge. If you would like to begin interviewing nannies, then there will be a $100 + HST, one-off booking fee. This is non-refundable, but it is deducted from your placement fee. The booking fee will be invoiced and is due before any interviews are set to take place.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div5\"></div>\r\n\r\nWhen you have decided on a nanny, we will assist you to write up a job offer. During this process, we will invoice you for the remainder of the placement fee (minus the $150 booking fee). Bumble Bees Nanny agency will also assist you in drawing up a contract which both parents and nanny will sign.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-table\">\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,200 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Full time (Over 36 hours a week) Permanent Placement. If two families come to Bumble Bees Nannies for a Nanny Share, then the placement fee is half each</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,000 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Part time (Under 35 hours a week) Permanent Placement</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,000 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Per family for a Nanny Share when Bumble Bees Nannies finds the other family as well as the nanny</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Two-Month Temporary Placemment</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">After School Care (Under 25 hours a week)</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$200 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Register with the Emergency Babysitting</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$150 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">In home consultation fee (which is deducted from the final placement fee)</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$150 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Booking fee (which is deducted from the final placement fee)</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Fee Structure','','publish','open','open','','fee-structure','','','2012-12-02 01:55:42','2012-12-02 01:55:42','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=190',0,'page','',0),(191,1,'2012-11-27 03:22:46','2012-11-27 03:22:46','Bumble Bees Nannies will email resumes for you to look at without charge. If you would like to begin interviewing nannies, then there will be a $100 + HST, one-off booking fee.\n\nThis is non-refundable, but it is deducted from your placement fee. The booking fee will be invoiced and is due before any interviews are set to take place.\n\nWhen you have decided on a nanny, we will assist you in drawing up a contract which both parents and nanny will sign. At this time, we will invoice you for 50% of the balance of the placement fee (minus the $100 booking fee). The balance of the placement fee is due no later than 3 days before the nanny\'s start date.','Fee Structure','','inherit','open','open','','190-revision','','','2012-11-27 03:22:46','2012-11-27 03:22:46','',190,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/190-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(192,1,'2012-11-27 03:24:06','2012-11-27 03:24:06',' ','','','publish','open','open','','192','','','2012-12-06 02:04:53','2012-12-06 02:04:53','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=192',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(193,1,'2012-12-02 01:55:33','2012-12-02 01:55:33','Bumble Bees Nannies will email resumes for you to look at without charge. If you would like to begin interviewing nannies, then there will be a $100 + HST, one-off booking fee. This is non-refundable, but it is deducted from your placement fee. The booking fee will be invoiced and is due before any interviews are set to take place.\n\n<div class=\"divider div5\"></div>\n\nWhen you have decided on a nanny, we will assist you to write up a job offer. During this process, we will invoice you for the remainder of the placement fee (minus the $150 booking fee). Bumble Bees Nanny agency will also assist you in drawing up a contract which both parents and nanny will sign.\n\n<div class=\"fee-table\">\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,200 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Full time (Over 36 hours a week) Permanent Placement. If two families come to Bumble Bees Nannies for a Nanny Share, then the placement fee is half each</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,000 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Part time (Under 35 hours a week) Permanent Placement</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,000 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Per family for a Nanny Share when Bumble Bees Nannies finds the other family as well as the nanny</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Two-Month Temporary Placemment</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">After School Care (Under 25 hours a week)</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$200 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Register with the Emergency Babysitting</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$150 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">In home consultation fee (which is deducted from the final placement fee)</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\n<div class=\"cost\">$150 + HST</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Booking fee (which is deducted from the </div>\n</div>\n\n</div>','Fee Structure','','inherit','open','open','','190-autosave','','','2012-12-02 01:55:33','2012-12-02 01:55:33','',190,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/190-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(194,1,'2012-11-27 03:23:37','2012-11-27 03:23:37','Bumble Bees Nannies will email resumes for you to look at without charge. If you would like to begin interviewing nannies, then there will be a $100 + HST, one-off booking fee.\r\n\r\nThis is non-refundable, but it is deducted from your placement fee. The booking fee will be invoiced and is due before any interviews are set to take place.\r\n\r\nWhen you have decided on a nanny, we will assist you in drawing up a contract which both parents and nanny will sign. At this time, we will invoice you for 50% of the balance of the placement fee (minus the $100 booking fee). The balance of the placement fee is due no later than 3 days before the nanny\'s start date.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Fee Structure','','inherit','open','open','','190-revision-2','','','2012-11-27 03:23:37','2012-11-27 03:23:37','',190,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/190-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(195,1,'2012-11-27 03:26:51','2012-11-27 03:26:51','Bumble Bees Nannies will email resumes for you to look at without charg