h you with a nanny, not only by interests and family requirements, but also by personalities.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Nanny Search</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has received the application form, she will start looking for nannies who suit your needs and wants. During this process, we will keep in regular contact with you, updating you on the progress.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Interview Process</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has found nannies that we think will suit what you are looking for, you will be emailed resumes to read through as well as our own personal thoughts about why the nanny would suit your family. If you are interested in the nannies, then an interview will be setup. During this stage, a Booking Fee will be invoiced to you.\r\n\r\nOnce you have had your interviews and have decided on a  nanny, then a Nanny Trial will be arranged. This is so that the family and nanny get to know each other before a job offer is made.\r\n\r\n<strong>7. Nanny Trials</strong>\r\n\r\nRichelle recommends a trial so that the family can see the nanny interact with the children and family and for the nanny to see how the parents interact with their children. It should be a relaxing time, so the nanny can settle in and feel comfortable. It is recommended that the family pay the nanny for this time, minimum wage and last between 3-4 hours or to 4-5 days, depending on how well you feel it is going.\r\n\r\n<strong>8. Final Steps</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce you have decided on a nanny, then we can make a job offer to the nanny. If she accepts, then Bumble Bees Nannies will write a contract for you and the nanny can start.\r\n\r\nYou will receive a more descriptive \'Step-by-Step\' when we contact you so you know in detail how it works.','Families Step-By-Step','','inherit','open','open','','187-revision-2','','','2012-11-27 03:11:45','2012-11-27 03:11:45','',187,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/187-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(197,1,'2012-11-27 03:51:02','2012-11-27 03:51:02','<h4 id=\"live-out-nannies\">Live-Out Nannies</h4>\r\nLooking for someone to look after your child/children weekdays while you are at work? A nanny may be the best option for you.\r\n\r\nA nanny can be full time, part time or temporary. Nannies are generally sole charge, meaning that they are the only caregiver present with your child/ren.\r\n\r\nFull-time Live-out nannies work around 8-10 hours a day, Monday - Friday. With a Live-Out Nanny, additional babysitting outside of the standard schedule can be provided by agreement or contract (at additional cost).\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies have the qualifications you are looking for, including Early Childhood Education credits and years of childcare experience. A nanny can take care of a broad range of responsibilities, including just about everything related to your children:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Playing and Entertaining</li>\r\n	<li>Creating stimulating environments</li>\r\n	<li>Making sure that everything is age appropriate</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing play dates, sports and activities</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning the children\'s rooms/bathrooms and toys</li>\r\n	<li>Helping with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Cooking for the children and associated kitchen cleanup</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing and taking children to their doctors/dentist/hair appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Children\'s laundry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"mothers-help\">After School Care</h4>\r\nBumble Bees Nannies can provide quality After School Care. They will pick up your children from school, organize after school activities, help children with their homework, cook dinner and make sure all information from school is given to parents.\r\n\r\nWe usually try and place daycare teachers who have morning jobs or university students who are completing their degrees, ECE diplomas, Nursing students, psychology that are looking to work as After School Nannies to earn extra money.\r\n<h4 id=\"nanny-share\">Nanny Share</h4>\r\nCheck our <a title=\"Nanny Share Family Finder\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/nanny-share/\">Nanny Share</a> section for more information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Childcare Options','','publish','open','open','','childcare-options','','','2012-12-02 02:12:42','2012-12-02 02:12:42','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=197',0,'page','',0),(198,1,'2012-11-27 03:50:05','2012-11-27 03:50:05','<h4>Live-Out Nannies</h4>\nLooking for someone to look after your child/children weekdays while you are at work? A nanny may be the best option for you.\n\nA nanny can be full time, part time or temporary. Nannies are generally sole charge, meaning that they are the only caregiver present with your child/ren.\n\nFull-time Live-out nannies work around 8-10 hours a day, Monday - Friday. With a Live-Out Nanny, additional babysitting outside of the standard schedule can be provided by agreement or contract (at additional cost).\n\nBumble Bees Nannies have the qualifications you are looking for, including Early Childhood Education credits and years of childcare experience. A nanny can take care of a broad range of responsibilities, including just about everything related to your children:\n<ul>\n	<li>Playing and Entertaining</li>\n	<li>Creating stimulating environments</li>\n	<li>Making sure that everything is age appropriate</li>\n	<li>Organizing play dates, sports and activities</li>\n	<li>Cleaning the children\'s rooms/bathrooms and toys</li>\n	<li>Helping with homework</li>\n	<li>Cooking for the children and associated kitchen cleanup</li>\n	<li>Organizing and taking children to their doctors/dentist/hair appointments</li>\n	<li>Children\'s laundry</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Mother\'s Help</h4>\nNeed an extra pair of hands to help you with your children during the day? A Bumble Bees Mother\'s Helper can work hours similar to a nanny or a part time or be temporary. A mother\'s help is someone who is newer to childcare, with more limited experience. They are not left in sole charge of children for extended periods - they are there to look after the children alongside the parents, or alone with the children for a limited time when the parents are busy. A mother\'s helper can help with household chores such as emptying the dishwasher, folding laundry and grocery shopping. The Mother\'s help duties can vary and will be agreed upon and clarified by contract, by both mother\'s help and employer. Mother\'s helpers generally do not provide housekeeping services.\n<h4>After School Care</h4>\nBumble Bees Nannies can provide quality After School Care. They will pick up your children from school, organize after school activities, help children with their homework, cook dinner and make sure all information from school is given to parents.\n\nWe usually try and place daycare teachers who have morning jobs or university students who are completing their degrees, ECE diplomas, Nursing students, psychology that are looking to work as After School Nannies\n\n&nbsp;','Childcare Options','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision','','','2012-11-27 03:50:05','2012-11-27 03:50:05','',197,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/197-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(199,1,'2012-11-27 03:51:20','2012-11-27 03:51:20',' ','','','publish','open','open','','199','','','2012-12-06 02:04:53','2012-12-06 02:04:53','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=199',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(200,1,'2012-11-27 03:58:28','2012-11-27 03:58:28','If you have the right experience, personality and knowledge, we can help you find your perfect job as a LiveIn Nanny, Live-Out Nanny, Mother\'s Helper, After School care or Nanny-share, permanent or temporary, full time or part time. If you are newly qualified or wish to gain further experience, there are many opportunities to explore, such as being a mother\'s helper or even babysitting.\n\nIf you have the right qualifications and experience, and you successfully complete a series of checks and the interview process, you will be registered as a Bumble Bees Nannies Childcare Professional.\n\n\"Welcome to Bumble Bees Nannies. Being a nanny is a fulfilling and professional career choice, working with children on a one to one level, watching them grow up and develop into little adults. You help them through their stages of development and support them in their everyday choices as they get older. I am here to help you find a great family to work with so you also can enjoy these great experiences like I have. Through my seven years of nanny experience I can offer you extra advice and help when deciding a family/job, from interview advice to finding childcare groups in your neighbourhood. I want to help nannies, and share my knowledge and skills - like others have done for me\"\n\n- Richelle Assenberg, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>','Caregivers','','inherit','open','open','','35-autosave','','','2012-11-27 03:58:28','2012-11-27 03:58:28','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/35-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(201,1,'2012-11-07 02:27:27','2012-11-07 02:27:27','Here is a nanny page','Nanny','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-2','','','2012-11-07 02:27:27','2012-11-07 02:27:27','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/35-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(202,1,'2012-11-27 04:01:39','2012-11-27 04:01:39','<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Register online for free - it just takes 2 minutes and attach your resume or email your resume directly to Richelle</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">If you have enough experience or qualifications, Bumble Bees Nannies will email you an application form and interview times when we are available to meet you</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">The application form needs to be filled out as descriptive as possible</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Once the interview has taken place, your references, passports and police/identity papers will be checked.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">If all goes well, you will be contacted to become a Bumble Bees Nannies Childcare Professional</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Bumble Bees Nannies will call or email you with potential opportunities</span></li>\r\n</ul>','Caregivers Step-By-Step','','publish','open','open','','caregivers-step-by-step','','','2012-11-30 04:30:34','2012-11-30 04:30:34','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=202',0,'page','',0),(203,1,'2012-11-27 04:01:05','2012-11-27 04:01:05','<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Register online for free - it just takes 2 minutes and attach your resume or email your resume directly to Richelle</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">If you have enough experience or qualifications, Bumble Bees Nannies will email you an application form and interview times when we are available to meet you</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">The application form needs to be filled out as descriptive as possible</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Once the interview has taken place, your references, passports and police/identity papers will be checked.</span></li>\n</ul>','Caregivers Step-By-Step','','inherit','open','open','','202-revision','','','2012-11-27 04:01:05','2012-11-27 04:01:05','',202,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/202-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(204,1,'2012-11-27 04:02:16','2012-11-27 04:02:16','','Step-By-Step','','publish','open','open','','step-by-step-2','','','2012-12-06 02:04:54','2012-12-06 02:04:54','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=204',13,'nav_menu_item','',0),(205,1,'2012-11-27 04:10:46','2012-11-27 04:10:46','<h4>Nanny, Nanny/Share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>ECE or ECA or qualified nanny qualification (you must present this at the interview)</li>\r\n	<li>At least three years full-time Professional Childcare experience if you are not ECE qualified</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>After School Care</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor or studying at university (ECE, Nursing, Psychology)</li>\r\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to help with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Emergency Babysitter</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Studying ECE/ECA or many years childcare experience</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n	<li>Over 17 years old</li>\r\n</ul>','Requirements To Be A Bumble Bees Childcare Professional','','publish','open','open','','requirements-to-be-a-bumble-bees-childcare-professional','','','2012-12-03 01:51:18','2012-12-03 01:51:18','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=205',0,'page','',0),(206,1,'2012-11-27 04:09:53','2012-11-27 04:09:53','Nanny, Nanny/Share\n<ul>\n	<li>ECE or ECA or qualified nanny qualification (you must present this at the interview)</li>\n	<li>At least three years full-time Professional Childcare experience if you are not ECE qualified</li>\n	<li>At least two references</li>\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\n</ul>\nMother\'s Helper\n<ul>\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor</li>\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\n	<li>Willingness to learn and listen to the mother or father</li>\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\n</ul>\nAfter School Care\n<ul>\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor or studying at university (ECE, Nursing, Psychology)</li>\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\n	<li>Ability to help with homework</li>\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\n	<li>Recen Police check</li>\n</ul>\nEmergency Babysitter\n<ul>\n	<li>Studying ECE/ECA or many years</li>\n</ul>','Requirements To Be A Bumble Bees Childcare Professional','','inherit','open','open','','205-revision','','','2012-11-27 04:09:53','2012-11-27 04:09:53','',205,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/205-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(207,1,'2012-12-03 01:52:20','2012-12-03 01:52:20','<h4>Nanny, Nanny/Share</h4>\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n	<li>ECE or ECA or qualified nanny qualification (you must present this at the interview)</li>\n	<li>At least three years full-time Professional Childcare experience if you are not ECE qualified</li>\n	<li>At least two references</li>\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>After School Care</h4>\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor or studying at university (ECE, Nursing, Psychology)</li>\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\n	<li>Ability to help with homework</li>\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Emergency Babysitter</h4>\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n	<li>Studying ECE/ECA or many years childcare experience</li>\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\n	<li>Over 17 years old</li>\n</ul>','Requirements To Be A Bumble Bees Childcare Professional','','inherit','open','open','','205-autosave','','','2012-12-03 01:52:20','2012-12-03 01:52:20','',205,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/205-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(208,1,'2012-11-27 04:10:46','2012-11-27 04:10:46','Nanny, Nanny/Share\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ECE or ECA or qualified nanny qualification (you must present this at the interview)</li>\r\n	<li>At least three years full-time Professional Childcare experience if you are not ECE qualified</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMother\'s Helper\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor</li>\r\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\r\n	<li>Willingness to learn and listen to the mother or father</li>\r\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAfter School Care\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor or studying at university (ECE, Nursing, Psychology)</li>\r\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to help with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEmergency Babysitter\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Studying ECE/ECA or many years childcare experience</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n	<li>Over 17 years old</li>\r\n</ul>','Requirements To Be A Bumble Bees Childcare Professional','','inherit','open','open','','205-revision-2','','','2012-11-27 04:10:46','2012-11-27 04:10:46','',205,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/205-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(209,1,'2012-11-27 04:14:08','2012-11-27 04:14:08',' ','','','publish','open','open','','209','','','2012-12-06 02:04:54','2012-12-06 02:04:54','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=209',14,'nav_menu_item','',0),(210,1,'2012-11-27 04:16:15','2012-11-27 04:16:15','<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Written references from previous jobs and character references or phone numbers from at least two childcare positions</li>\r\n	<li>Photocopy of Birth Certificate, Passport and visa/work permit (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Current First Aid and CPR certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Degree/Diploma or Certificate from all your courses</li>\r\n	<li>Two passport sized photos - smiling would be great</li>\r\n</ul>','Interview Information','','publish','open','open','','interview-information','','','2012-11-30 04:30:19','2012-11-30 04:30:19','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=210',0,'page','',0),(211,1,'2012-11-27 04:15:21','2012-11-27 04:15:21','<ul>\n	<li>Written references from previous jobs and character references or phone numbers from at least two childcare positions</li>\n	<li>Photocopy of Birth Certificate, Passport and Visa/wor</li>\n</ul>','Interview Information','','inherit','open','open','','210-revision','','','2012-11-27 04:15:21','2012-11-27 04:15:21','',210,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/210-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(212,1,'2012-11-27 04:16:35','2012-11-27 04:16:35',' ','','','publish','open','open','','212','','','2012-12-06 02:04:54','2012-12-06 02:04:54','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=212',15,'nav_menu_item','',0),(213,1,'2012-11-07 02:00:52','2012-11-07 02:00:52','','another page','','inherit','open','open','','25-revision-2','','','2012-11-07 02:00:52','2012-11-07 02:00:52','',25,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/25-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(247,1,'2012-11-28 03:07:41','2012-11-28 03:07:41','','first job posting','','publish','closed','closed','','first-job-posting','','','2012-11-28 03:10:12','2012-11-28 03:10:12','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?post_type=job_vacancy&#038;p=247',0,'job_vacancy','',0),(248,1,'2012-11-07 02:01:10','2012-11-07 02:01:10','','test page','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-5','','','2012-11-07 02:01:10','2012-11-07 02:01:10','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(249,1,'2012-11-28 03:13:35','2012-11-28 03:13:35','Full Time job description perhaps...','Full Time','','publish','open','open','','full-time','','','2012-11-28 04:46:13','2012-11-28 04:46:13','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=249',0,'page','',0),(250,1,'2012-11-28 03:13:28','2012-11-28 03:13:28','','Full Time','','inherit','open','open','','249-revision','','','2012-11-28 03:13:28','2012-11-28 03:13:28','',249,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/249-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(251,1,'2012-11-28 03:13:55','2012-11-28 03:13:55','','Part Time','','publish','open','open','','part-time','','','2012-11-28 03:13:55','2012-11-28 03:13:55','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=251',0,'page','',0),(252,1,'2012-11-28 03:13:51','2012-11-28 03:13:51','','Part Time','','inherit','open','open','','251-revision','','','2012-11-28 03:13:51','2012-11-28 03:13:51','',251,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/251-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(253,1,'2012-11-28 03:14:09','2012-11-28 03:14:09','','After School Care','','publish','open','open','','after-school-care','','','2012-11-28 03:14:09','2012-11-28 03:14:09','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=253',0,'page','',0),(254,1,'2012-11-28 03:14:05','2012-11-28 03:14:05','','After School Care','','inherit','open','open','','253-revision','','','2012-11-28 03:14:05','2012-11-28 03:14:05','',253,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/253-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(257,1,'2012-11-28 03:15:05','2012-11-28 03:15:05','','Mother\'s Help','','publish','open','open','','mothers-help','','','2012-11-28 03:15:05','2012-11-28 03:15:05','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=257',0,'page','',0),(258,1,'2012-11-28 03:15:03','2012-11-28 03:15:03','','Mother\'s Help','','inherit','open','open','','257-revision','','','2012-11-28 03:15:03','2012-11-28 03:15:03','',257,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/257-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(260,1,'2012-11-28 03:16:15','2012-11-28 03:16:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','260','','','2012-12-06 02:04:54','2012-12-06 02:04:54','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=260',23,'nav_menu_item','',0),(261,1,'2012-11-28 03:16:15','2012-11-28 03:16:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','261','','','2012-12-06 02:04:54','2012-12-06 02:04:54','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=261',22,'nav_menu_item','',0),(262,1,'2012-11-28 03:16:15','2012-11-28 03:16:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','262','','','2012-12-06 02:04:54','2012-12-06 02:04:54','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=262',21,'nav_menu_item','',0),(263,1,'2012-11-28 04:04:14','2012-11-28 04:04:14','','','','publish','closed','closed','','263','','','2012-11-28 04:54:03','2012-11-28 04:54:03','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?post_type=job_vacancy&#038;p=263',0,'job_vacancy','',0),(264,1,'2012-11-28 03:13:35','2012-11-28 03:13:35','','Full Time','','inherit','open','open','','249-revision-2','','','2012-11-28 03:13:35','2012-11-28 03:13:35','',249,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/249-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(265,1,'2012-11-28 04:47:14','2012-11-28 04:47:14','Full Time job description perhaps...','Full Time','','inherit','open','open','','249-autosave','','','2012-11-28 04:47:14','2012-11-28 04:47:14','',249,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/249-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(266,1,'2012-11-20 22:15:03','2012-11-20 22:15:03','Welcome to the new Nanny Share Family Finder. Bumble Bees Nannies knows how difficult it is to find other families to share with. Now you can look here to find families and see what they are looking for.\r\n<h4>How It Works</h4>\r\nTo get your details on the Family Finder, you need to contact Richelle and fill out an application form. The application form will give you guidance on what you are looking for in a nanny.\r\n\r\nFrom there, you will get a family number and your basic details will be put online. Your personal details will stay confidential. If a family is interested to get in contact with you, I will only pass out your phone number or email address depending on which one you give permission for.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in a family you see below, please click the box.\r\n\r\nOnce you and the other family decide to work together and decide to use Bumble Bees Nannies, then I will use your application forms to look for a nanny for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"controls\"><button class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-sharing\';\">Families With A Shared Nanny</button><button class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-looking\';\">Families Looking For A Shared Nanny</button></div>','Nanny Share Family Finder','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-13','','','2012-11-20 22:15:03','2012-11-20 22:15:03','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(267,1,'2012-11-22 05:54:33','2012-11-22 05:54:33','<h4>Why Use A Nanny Agency?</h4>\r\n\"Bumble Bees Nannies will find the perfect nanny for your family. I personally evaluate the childcare needs of your family and together we\'ll find the best nanny with the right experience and personality to care for your little ones. Qualified nannies have so much to offer, helping children have a great start in life. From teaching children as they play, preparing them for school, giving them love and attention, Bumble Bees Nannies will use all their knowledge and experience to fulfill the children\'s needs, providing a healthy, educational and safe environment\"\r\n\r\n- <strong>Richelle Assenberg</strong>, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsing Bumble Bees Nannies will help you find your perfect nanny. Using our agency means that you don\'t have to do all the work which is involved in hiring someone to work with children; answering the many phone calls you will receive of interested caregivers looking for work or responding to all the emails, searching the internet daily, checking resumes and conducting many interviews. This work can take a lot of time up, let Bumble Bees Nannies do this all for you.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is alos registered with Toronto Police so we can conduct Vulnerable Person\'s Police Checks with written permission from the applicants.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is the place to go in Toronto when searching for excellence in childcare services for your family\r\n<h4>Positives Of Having A Nanny</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your child will receive more attention from the caregiver - one on one</li>\r\n	<li>Your child will develop a close bond with the nanny quicker than in a daycare</li>\r\n	<li>Your children will be able to go on trips on a regular basis, weekly or bi-weekly; parks, zoo, science centre, swimming</li>\r\n	<li>Consistency and routine of being with another child and nanny builds trust and stability</li>\r\n	<li>You are able to come home and your children have had their dinner and are ready to spend quality time with you. No daycare runs and then having to go home and still cook dinner for your children and get them ready for bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>What Differentiates Us?</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We will guide you through the process in finding the right childcare solution for your family</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies conducts face-to-face meetings with families, getting to know our clients and their childcare needs to facilitate the perfect nanny match</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies recommends have trials that are 2-4 days long to see if the nanny suits your family and to see if they fit in. This reduces the chance of nanny\'s not working out</li>\r\n	<li>3 Month Trials: If your nanny decides to leave, Bumble Bees Nannies will attempt to find a suitable replacement free of charge</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies will provide full support for families throughout the 3 Month Trial</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Customized, personal service</strong> - simply the best for your family!</li>\r\n</ul>','Families','','inherit','open','open','','154-revision-8','','','2012-11-22 05:54:33','2012-11-22 05:54:33','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/154-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(268,1,'2012-11-30 04:28:52','2012-11-30 04:28:52','<h4>Why Use A Nanny Agency?</h4>\r\n\"Bumble Bees Nannies will find the perfect nanny for your family. I personally evaluate the childcare needs of your family and together we\'ll find the best nanny with the right experience and personality to care for your little ones. Qualified nannies have so much to offer, helping children have a great start in life. From teaching children as they play, preparing them for school, giving them love and attention, Bumble Bees Nannies will use all their knowledge and experience to fulfill the children\'s needs, providing a healthy, educational and safe environment\"\r\n\r\n- <strong>Richelle Assenberg</strong>, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsing Bumble Bees Nannies will help you find your perfect nanny. Using our agency means that you don\'t have to do all the work which is involved in hiring someone to work with children; answering the many phone calls you will receive of interested caregivers looking for work or responding to all the emails, searching the internet daily, checking resumes and conducting many interviews. This work can take a lot of time up, let Bumble Bees Nannies do this all for you.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is alos registered with Toronto Police so we can conduct Vulnerable Person\'s Police Checks with written permission from the applicants.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is the place to go in Toronto when searching for excellence in childcare services for your family\r\n<h4>Positives Of Having A Nanny</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Your child will receive more attention from the caregiver - one on one</li>\r\n	<li>Your child will develop a close bond with the nanny quicker than in a daycare</li>\r\n	<li>Your children will be able to go on trips on a regular basis, weekly or bi-weekly; parks, zoo, science centre, swimming</li>\r\n	<li>Consistency and routine of being with another child and nanny builds trust and stability</li>\r\n	<li>You are able to come home and your children have had their dinner and are ready to spend quality time with you. No daycare runs and then having to go home and still cook dinner for your children and get them ready for bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>What Differentiates Us?</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We will guide you through the process in finding the right childcare solution for your family</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies conducts face-to-face meetings with families, getting to know our clients and their childcare needs to facilitate the perfect nanny match</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies recommends have trials that are 2-4 days long to see if the nanny suits your family and to see if they fit in. This reduces the chance of nanny\'s not working out</li>\r\n	<li>3 Month Trials: If your nanny decides to leave, Bumble Bees Nannies will attempt to find a suitable replacement free of charge</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies will provide full support for families throughout the 3 Month Trial</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Customized, personal service</strong> - simply the best for your family!</li>\r\n</ul>','Families','','inherit','open','open','','154-revision-9','','','2012-11-30 04:28:52','2012-11-30 04:28:52','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/154-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2012-11-23 03:18:01','2012-11-23 03:18:01','What is the screening process for nannies joining Bumble Bees Nannies?\r\n\r\nAt Bumble Bees Nannies, all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume, as well as an application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years experience, they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children and why they finished with their last employer. During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a  family.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>References</li>\r\n	<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\r\n	<li>Up to date Police Check</li>\r\n	<li>Drivers License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhile going through their resume/CV, we look for any loopholes/gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\r\n\r\nWith Bumble Bees Nannies doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount of nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates, so let Bumble Bees Nannies do all the work finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees Nannies aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\r\n\r\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees Nannies requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process, we are confident that we can find the right nanny for your family.','Nanny Screening Process','','inherit','open','open','','164-revision-2','','','2012-11-23 03:18:01','2012-11-23 03:18:01','',164,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/164-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(270,1,'2012-11-27 04:16:15','2012-11-27 04:16:15','<ul>\r\n	<li>Written references from previous jobs and character references or phone numbers from at least two childcare positions</li>\r\n	<li>Photocopy of Birth Certificate, Passport and visa/work permit (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Current First Aid and CPR certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Degree/Diploma or Certificate from all your courses</li>\r\n	<li>Two passport sized photos - smiling would be great</li>\r\n</ul>','Interview Information','','inherit','open','open','','210-revision-2','','','2012-11-27 04:16:15','2012-11-27 04:16:15','',210,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/210-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(271,1,'2012-11-27 04:01:39','2012-11-27 04:01:39','<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Register online for free - it just takes 2 minutes and attach your resume or email your resume directly to Richelle</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">If you have enough experience or qualifications, Bumble Bees Nannies will email you an application form and interview times when we are available to meet you</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">The application form needs to be filled out as descriptive as possible</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Once the interview has taken place, your references, passports and police/identity papers will be checked.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">If all goes well, you will be contacted to become a Bumble Bees Nannies Childcare Professional</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">Bumble Bees Nannies will call or email you with potential opportunities</span></li>\r\n</ul>','Caregivers Step-By-Step','','inherit','open','open','','202-revision-2','','','2012-11-27 04:01:39','2012-11-27 04:01:39','',202,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/202-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(272,1,'2012-11-27 04:13:38','2012-11-27 04:13:38','<h4>Nanny, Nanny/Share</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ECE or ECA or qualified nanny qualification (you must present this at the interview)</li>\r\n	<li>At least three years full-time Professional Childcare experience if you are not ECE qualified</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Mother\'s Helper</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor</li>\r\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\r\n	<li>Willingness to learn and listen to the mother or father</li>\r\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>After School Care</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor or studying at university (ECE, Nursing, Psychology)</li>\r\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to help with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Emergency Babysitter</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Studying ECE/ECA or many years childcare experience</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n	<li>Over 17 years old</li>\r\n</ul>','Requirements To Be A Bumble Bees Childcare Professional','','inherit','open','open','','205-revision-3','','','2012-11-27 04:13:38','2012-11-27 04:13:38','',205,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/205-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(273,1,'2012-11-27 03:36:17','2012-11-27 03:36:17','<strong>1. What your family needs from a childcare professional</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Do you need someone to help solely with your children or also run errands?</li>\r\n	<li>Do you need an extra pair of hands around the house to help with the children?</li>\r\n	<li>Does the child care professional need to be active and young at heart?</li>\r\n	<li>How many years experience would you like the nanny to have?</li>\r\n	<li>Is a driver necessary for school runs, after school activities or play dates?</li>\r\n	<li>Full or part time?</li>\r\n	<li>Would both parents be at work during the day so you need a very qualified nanny, with great communication skills?</li>\r\n	<li>Would you like your caregiver to have the same interests as you or your children?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>2. Shall I hire a Live-In or Live-Out Nanny?</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Live-In Nanny</strong>: The salary of a live-in nanny is lower because the food and accommodation is taken into account and there is extra room to accommodate the nanny (bedroom, living area, bathroom - which can be shared with the children). If a nanny lives with you, they need to have access to the kitchen and most areas of the house, tehy become a part of the family and a close bond with the nanny and family is usually developed quite quickly.\r\n\r\nA negative side to consider is the lack of privacy after hours and in weekends. Most nannies keep themselves busy and have a V in their living area, but they do need to share the kitchen and bathrooms with the family.\r\n\r\n<strong>Live-Out Nanny</strong>: There is a lack of space for a nanny to live with the family and the family want to keep their privacy, especially in the weekends and after hours. Most of the qualified and experienced nannies are live-out nannies, they have their own homes and families to go back to at the end of each day.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Contact Bumble Bees Nannies via Email or Phone</strong>\r\n\r\nFill in an <a title=\"Family Registration Form\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/family-registration/\">online form</a> with the basic details of your family needs and then we will contact you with further questions. Or email <a href=\"mailto:richelle@bumblebeesnannies.com\">Richelle</a> directly with a brief message on what you are looking for.\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Application Forms</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce this has been done, we will call you to discuss your needs and answer any questions you may have. An application form will t hen be emailed to you that you will need to fill out and email back. We use this to write job descriptions for the nannies to read and to help us get a sense of what you are looking for to make the match.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies likes to conduct face to face meetings with families as well as nannies so they can get a better idea of the family so we can match you with a nanny, not only by interests and family requirements, but also by personalities.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Nanny Search</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has received the application form, she will start looking for nannies who suit your needs and wants. During this process, we will keep in regular contact with you, updating you on the progress.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Interview Process</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has found nannies that we think will suit what you are looking for, you will be emailed resumes to read through as well as our own personal thoughts about why the nanny would suit your family. If you are interested in the nannies, then an interview will be setup. During this stage, a <a title=\"Fee Structure\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/fee-structure/\">Booking Fee</a> will be invoiced to you.\r\n\r\nOnce you have had your interviews and have decided on a  nanny, then a Nanny Trial will be arranged. This is so that the family and nanny get to know each other before a job offer is made.\r\n\r\n<strong>7. Nanny Trials</strong>\r\n\r\nRichelle recommends a trial so that the family can see the nanny interact with the children and family and for the nanny to see how the parents interact with their children. It should be a relaxing time, so the nanny can settle in and feel comfortable. It is recommended that the family pay the nanny for this time, minimum wage and last between 3-4 hours or to 4-5 days, depending on how well you feel it is going.\r\n\r\n<strong>8. Final Steps</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce you have decided on a nanny, then we can make a job offer to the nanny. If she accepts, then Bumble Bees Nannies will write a contract for you and the nanny can start.\r\n\r\nYou will receive a more descriptive \'Step-by-Step\' when we contact you so you know in detail how it works.','Families Step-By-Step','','inherit','open','open','','187-revision-3','','','2012-11-27 03:36:17','2012-11-27 03:36:17','',187,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/187-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(274,1,'2012-11-27 03:51:02','2012-11-27 03:51:02','<h4>Live-Out Nannies</h4>\r\nLooking for someone to look after your child/children weekdays while you are at work? A nanny may be the best option for you.\r\n\r\nA nanny can be full time, part time or temporary. Nannies are generally sole charge, meaning that they are the only caregiver present with your child/ren.\r\n\r\nFull-time Live-out nannies work around 8-10 hours a day, Monday - Friday. With a Live-Out Nanny, additional babysitting outside of the standard schedule can be provided by agreement or contract (at additional cost).\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies have the qualifications you are looking for, including Early Childhood Education credits and years of childcare experience. A nanny can take care of a broad range of responsibilities, including just about everything related to your children:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Playing and Entertaining</li>\r\n	<li>Creating stimulating environments</li>\r\n	<li>Making sure that everything is age appropriate</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing play dates, sports and activities</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning the children\'s rooms/bathrooms and toys</li>\r\n	<li>Helping with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Cooking for the children and associated kitchen cleanup</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing and taking children to their doctors/dentist/hair appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Children\'s laundry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Mother\'s Help</h4>\r\nNeed an extra pair of hands to help you with your children during the day? A Bumble Bees Mother\'s Helper can work hours similar to a nanny or a part time or be temporary. A mother\'s help is someone who is newer to childcare, with more limited experience. They are not left in sole charge of children for extended periods - they are there to look after the children alongside the parents, or alone with the children for a limited time when the parents are busy. A mother\'s helper can help with household chores such as emptying the dishwasher, folding laundry and grocery shopping. The Mother\'s help duties can vary and will be agreed upon and clarified by contract, by both mother\'s help and employer. Mother\'s helpers generally do not provide housekeeping services.\r\n<h4>After School Care</h4>\r\nBumble Bees Nannies can provide quality After School Care. They will pick up your children from school, organize after school activities, help children with their homework, cook dinner and make sure all information from school is given to parents.\r\n\r\nWe usually try and place daycare teachers who have morning jobs or university students who are completing their degrees, ECE diplomas, Nursing students, psychology that are looking to work as After School Nannies to earn extra money.\r\n\r\nNanny Share\r\n\r\nCheck our <a title=\"Nanny Share Family Finder\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/nanny-share/\">Nanny Share</a> section for more information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Childcare Options','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision-2','','','2012-11-27 03:51:02','2012-11-27 03:51:02','',197,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/197-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(275,1,'2012-12-01 21:44:33','2012-12-01 21:44:33','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Mauris leo dui, aliquet vitae scelerisque eget, laoreet sit amet libero. Aliquam erat volutpat. Suspendisse porttitor, risus vel fermentum semper, sapien nulla rhoncus nulla, a pulvinar orci nunc e