es Nannies has received the application form, we will start looking for nannies who suit your needs and wants. During this process, we will keep in regular contact with you, updating you on the progress.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Interview Process</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has found nannies that we think will suit what you are looking for, you will be emailed resumes to read through as well as our own personal thoughts about why the nanny would suit your family. If you are interested in the nannies, an interview will be setup. During this stage, a <a title=\"Fee Structure\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/fee-structure/\">Booking Fee</a> will be invoiced to you.\r\n\r\nOnce you have had your interviews and have decided on a  nanny, a Nanny Trial will be arranged. This is so that the family and nanny get to know each other before a job offer is made.\r\n\r\n<strong>7. Nanny Trials</strong>\r\n\r\nRichelle recommends a trial so that the family can see the nanny interact with the children and family and for the nanny to see how the parents interact with their children. It should be a relaxing time, so the nanny can settle in and feel comfortable. It is recommended that the family pay the nanny for this time, minimum wage and last between 3-4 hours or to 4-5 days, depending on how well you feel it is going.\r\n\r\n<strong>8. Final Steps</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce you have decided on a nanny, then we can make a job offer to the nanny. If she accepts, then Bumble Bees Nannies will write a contract for you and the nanny can start.\r\n\r\nYou will receive a more descriptive \'Step-by-Step\' when we contact you so you know in detail how it works.','Families Step-By-Step','','inherit','open','open','','187-revision-10','','','2012-12-02 01:21:08','2012-12-02 01:21:08','',187,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/187-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(300,1,'2012-12-02 01:26:52','2012-12-02 01:26:52','Bumble Bees is trying to improve the standard of Nanny Care in Toronto. From my experience I have seen the difference in having an EC Educator as a nanny. Learning the basics of Nannying comes very naturally and quickly to these teachers, they have the extra knowledge that is so important in the first 5 years of a child’s life.\r\n\r\nMany students completing their Bachelor in Education or Diploma in Early Childhood from recognized Colleges are looking to be nannies. They enjoy being nanny’s more because it involves one on one education and care. They get to educate and care for children to the best of their knowledge, to see your children grow and develop and to teach them.\r\n\r\nHaving a newly qualified teacher in your home is fantastic, they understand so much about children and specialize in Early Childhood development.\r\n\r\nEC students study Human Development theorists - Vygotsky, Piaget and Freund - who have spent many years researching how children learn.\r\n\r\nEarly Childhood students know\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ages and Stages in human development</li>\r\n	<li>Socialization skills</li>\r\n	<li>The different types of play</li>\r\n	<li>Age appropriate play.</li>\r\n	<li>Physical development (gross and fine motor).</li>\r\n	<li>Cognitive development</li>\r\n	<li>Emotional stages that children go through</li>\r\n	<li>They have a natural ability to observe children and ask questions</li>\r\n	<li>Understand to ask open ended questions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEarly Childhood teachers have that special touch. During their education they are placed in different settings such as day cares and primary schools and are there for around 3 months at a time. During this stage they practice their knowledge that they have learnt in the classroom and are watched and critiqued by their lectures.\r\n\r\nIn a Nanny and Nanny Share setting Early Childhood educators are affordable.','Early Childhood Educator As Your Nanny','','publish','open','open','','early-childhood-educator-as-your-nanny','','','2012-12-02 01:26:52','2012-12-02 01:26:52','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=300',0,'page','',0),(301,1,'2012-12-02 01:26:08','2012-12-02 01:26:08','Bumble Bees is trying to improve the standard of Nanny Care in Toronto. From my experience I have seen the difference in having an EC Educator as a nanny. Learning the basics of Nannying comes very naturally and quickly to these teachers, they have the extra knowledge that is so important in the first 5 years of a child’s life.\n\nMany students completing their Bachelor in Education or Diploma in Early Childhood from recognized Colleges are looking to be nannies. They enjoy being nanny’s more because it involves one on one education and care. They get to educate and care for children to the best of their knowledge, to see your children grow and develop and to teach them.\n\nHaving a newly qualified teacher in your home is fantastic, they understand so much about children and specialize in Early Childhood development.\n\nEC students study Human Development theorists - Vygotsky, Piaget and Freund - who have spent many years researching how children learn.\n\nEarly Childhood students know\n<ul>\n	<li>Ages and Stages in human development</li>\n	<li>Socialization skills</li>\n	<li>The different types of play</li>\n	<li>Age appropriate play.</li>\n	<li>Physical development (gross and fine motor).</li>\n	<li>Cognitive development</li>\n	<li>Emotional stages that children go through</li>\n	<li>They have a natural ability to observe children and ask questions</li>\n	<li>Understand to ask open ended questions</li>\n</ul>\nEarly Childhood teachers have that special touch. During their education they are placed in different settings-daycares, primary schools and are there for around 3 months at a time. During this stage they practice their knowledge that they have learnt in the classroom and are watched and critiqued by their lectures.\n\nIn a Nanny and Nanny Share setting Early Childhood educators are affordable.','Early Childhood Educator As Your Nanny','','inherit','open','open','','300-revision','','','2012-12-02 01:26:08','2012-12-02 01:26:08','',300,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/300-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(302,1,'2012-12-02 01:28:12','2012-12-02 01:28:12','','Early Childhood Educator','','publish','open','open','','early-childhood-educator','','','2012-12-06 02:04:53','2012-12-06 02:04:53','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=302',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(303,1,'2012-12-02 01:30:46','2012-12-02 01:30:46','<h4>Employer Obligations</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Nanny taxes. The family is responsible for paying the nanny’s taxes.</li>\r\n	<li>Families are also recommended and responsible to take out Workers Safety and Insurance (WSIB) when employing a nanny who will be in your home.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Nanny’s Expectations from the Family</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li> To build up a relation of trust between the Nanny and the Parents having good and regular communication</li>\r\n	<li>Support the Nanny’s “authority” in setting limits with the child(ren)</li>\r\n	<li>Provide a safe child-proofed home</li>\r\n	<li>Respect the Nanny’s privacy and shall be treated with full professional courtesy. In return the Nanny will treat the Parents with due respect</li>\r\n</ul>','Obligations','','publish','open','open','','obligations','','','2012-12-02 01:30:46','2012-12-02 01:30:46','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=303',0,'page','',0),(304,1,'2012-12-02 01:30:31','2012-12-02 01:30:31','<h4>Employer Obligations</h4>\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n	<li>Nanny taxes. The family is responsible for paying the nanny’s taxes.</li>\n	<li>Families are also recommended and responsible to take out Workers Safety and Insurance (WSIB) when employing a nanny who will be in your home.</li>\n</ul>\nNanny’s Expectations from the Family:\n<ul>\n	<li> To build up a relation of trust between the Nanny and the Parents having good and regular communication</li>\n	<li>Support the Nanny’s “authority” in setting limits with the child(ren)</li>\n	<li>Provide a safe child-proofed home</li>\n	<li>Respect the Nanny’s privacy and shall be treated with full professional courtesy. In return the Nanny will treat the Parents with due respect</li>\n</ul>','Obligations','','inherit','open','open','','303-revision','','','2012-12-02 01:30:31','2012-12-02 01:30:31','',303,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/303-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(305,1,'2012-12-02 01:31:03','2012-12-02 01:31:03',' ','','','publish','open','open','','305','','','2012-12-06 02:04:53','2012-12-06 02:04:53','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=305',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(306,1,'2012-12-02 00:49:17','2012-12-02 00:49:17','Bumble Bees Nannies will email resumes for you to look at without charge. If you would like to begin interviewing nannies, then there will be a $100 + HST, one-off booking fee.\r\n\r\nThis is non-refundable, but it is deducted from your placement fee. The booking fee will be invoiced and is due before any interviews are set to take place.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div5\"></div>\r\n\r\nWhen you have decided on a nanny, we will assist you in drawing up a contract which both parents and nanny will sign. At this time, we will invoice you for 50% of the balance of the placement fee (minus the $100 booking fee). The balance of the placement fee is due no later than 3 days before the nanny\'s start date.\r\n<div class=\"fee-table\">\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,000 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Full time (Over 30 hours a week) Permanent Placement. If two families come to Bumble Bees Nannies for a Nanny Share, then the placement fee is half each</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Part time (Under 29 hours a week) Permanent Placement</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Per family for a Nanny Share when Bumble Bees Nannies finds the other family as well as the nanny</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$500 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Two-Month Temporary Placemment</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$500 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">After School Care</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$50 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Register with the Emergency Babysitting</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Fee Structure','','inherit','open','open','','190-revision-5','','','2012-12-02 00:49:17','2012-12-02 00:49:17','',190,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/190-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(307,1,'2012-12-02 02:04:50','2012-12-02 02:04:50','<h4>Nanny Pay Scale</h4>\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours.\n\nAn estimated cost of a <a title=\"Childcare Options\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/childcare-options/#live-out-nannies\">Live-out</a> nanny:\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n	<li>Part-time nannies ( less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12-$20 an hour</li>\n	<li>35-40 hour week- between $ 450-550 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\n	<li>40-50 hour week- between $500-$650 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\n</ul>\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny’s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\n\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\n\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\n\nTo pay your nanny you will need to apply for a Business number with The Canadian Revenue Agency. This is a very simple process. Once this has been done you can either use The Canadian revenue agency or use Bumble Bees Nannies’ new Nanny Payroll service. \n\n<h4>Bumble Bees Nannies Payroll</h4>\n<div class=\"payroll\">\nBumble Bees Nannies is now offering a new service: Nanny Payroll. We will start this service in January 2013. This service will reduce all your worry with paying your nanny.\n\nFor $300 per year, we\'ll help take care of:\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n<li>Calculating your nanny\'s gross net pay</li>\n<li>Nanny direct \n','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-autosave','','','2012-12-02 02:04:50','2012-12-02 02:04:50','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(308,1,'2012-11-23 03:27:06','2012-11-23 03:27:06','The required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours. Live-out and Live-in nannies receive a different salary because the living costs (accommodation and food) are taken into account for Live-in nannies.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a Live-out nanny:\r\n\r\nPart-time nannies (less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12 - $20 an hour.\r\n\r\n35-40 hour week - between $450 - $500 per week, net.\r\n\r\n40-50 hour week - between $500 - $600 per week, net.\r\n\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny\'s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nThis can be done through the Canadian Revenue Agency or with Bumble Bees Nannies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-3','','','2012-11-23 03:27:06','2012-11-23 03:27:06','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(309,1,'2012-12-02 02:00:49','2012-12-02 02:00:49','<h4>Nanny Pay Scale</h4>\r\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a <a title=\"Childcare Options\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/childcare-options/#live-out-nannies\">Live-out</a> nanny:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Part-time nannies ( less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12-$20 an hour</li>\r\n	<li>35-40 hour week- between $ 450-550 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n	<li>40-50 hour week- between $500-$650 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny’s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n\r\nTax Information\r\n\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nThis can be done through the Canadian Revenue Agency or with Bumble Bees Nannies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-4','','','2012-12-02 02:00:49','2012-12-02 02:00:49','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(310,1,'2012-12-02 02:05:40','2012-12-02 02:05:40','<h4>Nanny Pay Scale</h4>\r\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a <a title=\"Childcare Options\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/childcare-options/#live-out-nannies\">Live-out</a> nanny:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Part-time nannies ( less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12-$20 an hour</li>\r\n	<li>35-40 hour week- between $ 450-550 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n	<li>40-50 hour week- between $500-$650 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny’s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n\r\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\r\n\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nTo pay your nanny you will need to apply for a Business number with The Canadian Revenue Agency. This is a very simple process. Once this has been done you can either use The Canadian revenue agency or use Bumble Bees Nannies’ new Nanny Payroll service. \r\n\r\n<h4>Bumble Bees Nannies Payroll</h4>\r\n<div class=\"payroll\">\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is now offering a new service: Nanny Payroll. We will start this service in January 2013. This service will reduce all your worry with paying your nanny.\r\n\r\nFor $300 per year, we\'ll help take care of:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n<li>Calculating your nanny\'s gross net pay</li>\r\n<li>Nanny direct deposit</li>\r\n<li>Pay the CRA remittances on time on your behalf</li>\r\n<li>Issue a T4 at year end</li>\r\n<li>Issue a Record of Employment for your  nanny at the end of employment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-5','','','2012-12-02 02:05:40','2012-12-02 02:05:40','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(311,1,'2012-12-01 22:25:10','2012-12-01 22:25:10','<h4 id=\"live-out-nannies\">Live-Out Nannies</h4>\r\nLooking for someone to look after your child/children weekdays while you are at work? A nanny may be the best option for you.\r\n\r\nA nanny can be full time, part time or temporary. Nannies are generally sole charge, meaning that they are the only caregiver present with your child/ren.\r\n\r\nFull-time Live-out nannies work around 8-10 hours a day, Monday - Friday. With a Live-Out Nanny, additional babysitting outside of the standard schedule can be provided by agreement or contract (at additional cost).\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies have the qualifications you are looking for, including Early Childhood Education credits and years of childcare experience. A nanny can take care of a broad range of responsibilities, including just about everything related to your children:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Playing and Entertaining</li>\r\n	<li>Creating stimulating environments</li>\r\n	<li>Making sure that everything is age appropriate</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing play dates, sports and activities</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning the children\'s rooms/bathrooms and toys</li>\r\n	<li>Helping with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Cooking for the children and associated kitchen cleanup</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing and taking children to their doctors/dentist/hair appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Children\'s laundry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"mothers-help\">Mother\'s Help</h4>\r\nNeed an extra pair of hands to help you with your children during the day? A Bumble Bees Mother\'s Helper can work hours similar to a nanny or a part time or be temporary. A mother\'s help is someone who is newer to childcare, with more limited experience. They are not left in sole charge of children for extended periods - they are there to look after the children alongside the parents, or alone with the children for a limited time when the parents are busy. A mother\'s helper can help with household chores such as emptying the dishwasher, folding laundry and grocery shopping. The Mother\'s help duties can vary and will be agreed upon and clarified by contract, by both mother\'s help and employer. Mother\'s helpers generally do not provide housekeeping services.\r\n<h4 id=\"after-school-care\">After School Care</h4>\r\nBumble Bees Nannies can provide quality After School Care. They will pick up your children from school, organize after school activities, help children with their homework, cook dinner and make sure all information from school is given to parents.\r\n\r\nWe usually try and place daycare teachers who have morning jobs or university students who are completing their degrees, ECE diplomas, Nursing students, psychology that are looking to work as After School Nannies to earn extra money.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"nanny-share\">Nanny Share</h4>\r\n\r\nCheck our <a title=\"Nanny Share Family Finder\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/nanny-share/\">Nanny Share</a> section for more information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Childcare Options','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision-4','','','2012-12-01 22:25:10','2012-12-01 22:25:10','',197,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/197-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2012-11-28 03:12:54','2012-11-28 03:12:54','Here are the job vacancies, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...','Job Vacancies','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-6','','','2012-11-28 03:12:54','2012-11-28 03:12:54','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(313,1,'2012-12-02 02:34:22','2012-12-02 02:34:22','Here is the Job Vacancies description, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Full Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/full-time/\">Full Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Part Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/part-time/\">Part Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"After School Care\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/after-school-care/\">After School Care</a>','Job Vacancies','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-7','','','2012-12-02 02:34:22','2012-12-02 02:34:22','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(314,1,'2012-12-02 02:35:03','2012-12-02 02:35:03','Here is the Job Vacancies description, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...\r\n\r\n<a class=\"btn\" title=\"Full Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/full-time/\">Full Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Part Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/part-time/\">Part Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"After School Care\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/after-school-care/\">After School Care</a>','Job Vacancies','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-8','','','2012-12-02 02:35:03','2012-12-02 02:35:03','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(315,1,'2012-12-02 02:35:29','2012-12-02 02:35:29','Here is the Job Vacancies description, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...\r\n\r\n<div class=\"controls\">\r\n<a class=\"btn\" title=\"Full Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/full-time/\">Full Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a class=\"btn\" title=\"Part Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/part-time/\">Part Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a class=\"btn\" title=\"After School Care\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/after-school-care/\">After School Care</a>\r\n</div>','Job Vacancies','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-9','','','2012-12-02 02:35:29','2012-12-02 02:35:29','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(316,1,'2012-12-02 02:39:10','2012-12-02 02:39:10','Here is where you contact Bumble Bees Nannies to get in touch with a particular family.','Contact Family','','publish','open','open','','contact-family','','','2012-12-02 02:39:10','2012-12-02 02:39:10','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=316',0,'page','',0),(317,1,'2012-12-02 02:39:03','2012-12-02 02:39:03','','Contact Family','','inherit','open','open','','316-revision','','','2012-12-02 02:39:03','2012-12-02 02:39:03','',316,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/316-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2012-11-11 18:47:52','2012-11-11 18:47:52','Here\'s some introduction to the caregivers registration form page. This will need to be updated of course.','Caregiver Registration Form','','inherit','open','open','','58-revision-5','','','2012-11-11 18:47:52','2012-11-11 18:47:52','',58,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/58-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2012-12-03 01:26:13','2012-12-03 01:26:13','Here\'s some introduction to the caregivers registration form page. This will need to be updated of course.','Nanny Registration Form','','inherit','open','open','','58-revision-6','','','2012-12-03 01:26:13','2012-12-03 01:26:13','',58,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/58-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2012-12-03 01:26:54','2012-12-03 01:26:54','Here\'s some introduction to the caregivers registration form page. This will need to be updated of course.','Nanny Registration Form','','inherit','open','open','','58-revision-7','','','2012-12-03 01:26:54','2012-12-03 01:26:54','',58,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/58-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2012-12-02 00:46:03','2012-12-02 00:46:03','If you have the right experience, personality and knowledge, we can help you find your perfect job as a LiveIn Nanny, Live-Out Nanny, Mother\'s Helper, After School care or Nanny-share, permanent or temporary, full time or part time. If you are newly qualified or wish to gain further experience, there are many opportunities to explore, such as being a mother\'s helper or even babysitting.\r\n\r\nIf you have the right qualifications and experience, and you successfully complete a series of checks and the interview process, you will be registered as a Bumble Bees Nannies Childcare Professional.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div2\"></div>\r\n\r\n\"Welcome to Bumble Bees Nannies. Being a nanny is a fulfilling and professional career choice, working with children on a one to one level, watching them grow up and develop into little adults. You help them through their stages of development and support them in their everyday choices as they get older. I am here to help you find a great family to work with so you also can enjoy these great experiences like I have. Through my seven years of nanny experience I can offer you extra advice and help when deciding a family/job, from interview advice to finding childcare groups in your neighbourhood. I want to help nannies, and share my knowledge and skills - like others have done for me\"\r\n\r\n- <strong>Richelle Assenberg</strong>, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>','Caregivers','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-4','','','2012-12-02 00:46:03','2012-12-02 00:46:03','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/35-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(322,1,'2012-12-03 01:29:04','2012-12-03 01:29:04','If you have the right experience, personality and knowledge, we can help you find your perfect job as a LiveIn Nanny, Live-Out Nanny, Mother\'s Helper, After School care or Nanny-share, permanent or temporary, full time or part time. If you are newly qualified or wish to gain further experience, there are many opportunities to explore, such as being a mother\'s helper or even babysitting.\r\n\r\nIf you have the right qualifications and experience, and you successfully complete a series of checks and the interview process, you will be registered as a Bumble Bees Nannies Childcare Professional.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div2\"></div>\r\n\r\n\"Welcome to Bumble Bees Nannies. Being a nanny is a fulfilling and professional career choice, working with children on a one to one level, watching them grow up and develop into little adults. You help them through their stages of development and support them in their everyday choices as they get older. I am here to help you find a great family to work with so you also can enjoy these great experiences like I have. Through my seven years of nanny experience I can offer you extra advice and help when deciding a family/job, from interview advice to finding childcare groups in your neighbourhood. I want to help nannies, and share my knowledge and skills - like others have done for me\"\r\n\r\n- <strong>Richelle Assenberg</strong>, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>','Nannies','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-5','','','2012-12-03 01:29:04','2012-12-03 01:29:04','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/35-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(323,1,'2012-11-23 05:43:52','2012-11-23 05:43:52','Here\'s the family registration form.','Family Registration Form','','inherit','open','open','','71-revision-4','','','2012-11-23 05:43:52','2012-11-23 05:43:52','',71,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/71-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(324,1,'2012-12-03 01:44:04','2012-12-03 01:44:04','<div class=\"centered\">\r\n<h4>BUMBLE BEES NANNIES INC.</h4>\r\n<h4>CLIENT AGREEMENT</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li> OUR CONTRACT - Bumble Bees Nannies Inc. (“Bumble Bees”) is a referral agency only and nanny candidates presented to me/us are not employees of Bumble Bees.</li>\r\n	<li>NOTIFICATION - I/We agree to notify Bumble Bees immediately, either verbally or in writing, upon my/our acceptance of a nanny candidate for hire, and I/we agree to pay all fees to Bumble Bees as set out on the attached Fee schedule.</li>\r\n	<li>CANCELLATION PRIOR TO COMMENCEMENT OF EMPLOYMENT – I/We agree that if, after making an offer of employment to a nanny candidate who accepts the offer, the employment relationship is subsequently cancelled by me/us prior to the commencement of employment, that I/we will be responsible for payment of fees to Bumble Bees as follows:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n	<li>(a) If the cancellation occurs within 14 days or less of the scheduled commencement date of employment, the full fee owing shall be paid to Bumble Bees along with an additional payment in respect of one week’s salary to the nanny.</li>\r\n	<li>(b) If the cancellation occurs 15 days or more from the scheduled commencement date of employment, a fee of $200.00 shall be payable to Bumble Bees.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>REPLACEMENT - Bumble Bees will make every effort to provide a replacement nanny, on a one-time basis, without additional charge, in the event that the employment of an accepted nanny is terminated within the first 3 months of employment provided that:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees is notified within 3 days’ of the nanny’s termination; and</li>\r\n	<li>All applicable fees due to Bumble Bees have been paid according to the Fee schedule; and</li>\r\n	<li>The nanny has terminated the employment relationship; or</li>\r\n	<li>You have terminated the employment relationship for legal cause; or</li>\r\n	<li>The nanny and/or you feel that the relationship is not working out; or</li>\r\n	<li>If the nanny has terminated the employment relationship, it is not because of unreasonable demands being made by you or because there has been a change in the job description, hours, pay or job location originally agreed to between you and the nanny.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>THIRD PARTY INTRODUCTION - I/We agree to notify Bumble Bees immediately, either verbally or in writing, if a nanny candidate presented by Bumble Bees has previously been introduced to me/us by a third party. Otherwise, I/we acknowledge and agree that Bumble Bees will be considered to have introduced the nanny candidate to me/us and the relevant Fee shall be payable to Bumble Bees.</li>\r\n	<li>I/WE ARE THE EMPLOYER - I/We understand that I/we will be the employer of the selected nanny candidate that I/we will be responsible for entering into an employment contract with the nanny, paying all wages and benefits (if any)to the nanny, making all relevant employment deductions and remittances to the relevant government department, and providing all employment-related documentation to the nanny, as required by and in accordance with all employment and income tax laws in effect from time to time in the province of Ontario.</li>\r\n	<li>SUITABILITY AND REFERENCES – I/We understand that while Bumble Bees endeavours to ensure the suitability of the nanny candidates provided, the final decision to employ a nanny candidate is my/our responsibility and Bumble Bees does not warrant the suitability, honesty, capability or character of any nanny candidate introduced to me/us. Accordingly, I/we understand that I/we must:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n	<li>(a) Satisfy myself/ourselves as to the overall suitability of the nanny for my/our family;</li>\r\n	<li>(b) Check the references provided by a nanny candidate prior to making an offer of employment; and</li>\r\n	<li>(c) Verify the identification, work status, qualifications, and any other required criteria of the nanny candidate as would a prudent employer.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>INSURANCE - I/We will ensure that I/we have adequate insurance coverage for any possible losses sustained as a result of the employment of a child care worker in my/our home.</li>\r\n	<li>ADDITIONAL ADVICE MAY BE NECESSARY - While Bumble Bees offers assistance in setting up the employment relationship with any nanny candidate, I/we understand that we are ultimately responsible as employers, and will seek any such additional legal, accounting, immigration or other advice as required.</li>\r\n	<li>CONFIDENTIALITY - I/We agree to keep all information concerning nanny candidates confidential. I/We agree not to disclose any information concerning the nanny candidates provided by Bumble Bees to third parties without the express written consent of Bumble Bees. I/We acknowledge and agree that should unauthorized disclosure of such information be made to a third party resulting in the employment of a nanny candidate first introduced to me by Bumble Bees, that I may responsible to Bumble Bees for any and all fees owing.</li>\r\n	<li>LIABILITY – I/We agree that Bumble Bees will not be held liable for any claim by me/us for any loss or damage which may be incurred by us, howsoever caused, as a result of the introduction to or employment by me/us of any nanny candidate, or due the failure of Bumble Bees to introduce any nanny candidate to me/us.</li>\r\n	<li>ACCEPTANCE - By signing below I/we acknowledge having read, understood and agree to the above terms and conditions.</li>\r\n</ol>','Terms & Conditions','','publish','open','open','','terms-conditions','','','2012-12-03 01:46:34','2012-12-03 01:46:34','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=324',0,'page','',0),(325,1,'2012-12-03 