nt to a nanny candidate who accepts the offer, the employment relationship is subsequently cancelled by me/us prior to the commencement of employment, that I/we will be responsible for payment of fees to Bumble Bees as follows:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n	<li>(a) If the cancellation occurs within 14 days or less of the scheduled commencement date of employment, the full fee owing shall be paid to Bumble Bees along with an additional payment in respect of one week’s salary to the nanny.</li>\r\n	<li>(b) If the cancellation occurs 15 days or more from the scheduled commencement date of employment, a fee of $200.00 shall be payable to Bumble Bees.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>REPLACEMENT - Bumble Bees will make every effort to provide a replacement nanny, on a one-time basis, without additional charge, in the event that the employment of an accepted nanny is terminated within the first 3 months of employment provided that:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees is notified within 3 days’ of the nanny’s termination; and</li>\r\n	<li>All applicable fees due to Bumble Bees have been paid according to the Fee schedule; and</li>\r\n	<li>The nanny has terminated the employment relationship; or</li>\r\n	<li>You have terminated the employment relationship for legal cause; or</li>\r\n	<li>The nanny and/or you feel that the relationship is not working out; or</li>\r\n	<li>If the nanny has terminated the employment relationship, it is not because of unreasonable demands being made by you or because there has been a change in the job description, hours, pay or job location originally agreed to between you and the nanny.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>THIRD PARTY INTRODUCTION - I/We agree to notify Bumble Bees immediately, either verbally or in writing, if a nanny candidate presented by Bumble Bees has previously been introduced to me/us by a third party. Otherwise, I/we acknowledge and agree that Bumble Bees will be considered to have introduced the nanny candidate to me/us and the relevant Fee shall be payable to Bumble Bees.</li>\r\n	<li>I/WE ARE THE EMPLOYER - I/We understand that I/we will be the employer of the selected nanny candidate that I/we will be responsible for entering into an employment contract with the nanny, paying all wages and benefits (if any)to the nanny, making all relevant employment deductions and remittances to the relevant government department, and providing all employment-related documentation to the nanny, as required by and in accordance with all employment and income tax laws in effect from time to time in the province of Ontario.</li>\r\n	<li>SUITABILITY AND REFERENCES – I/We understand that while Bumble Bees endeavours to ensure the suitability of the nanny candidates provided, the final decision to employ a nanny candidate is my/our responsibility and Bumble Bees does not warrant the suitability, honesty, capability or character of any nanny candidate introduced to me/us. Accordingly, I/we understand that I/we must:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n	<li>(a) Satisfy myself/ourselves as to the overall suitability of the nanny for my/our family;</li>\r\n	<li>(b) Check the references provided by a nanny candidate prior to making an offer of employment; and</li>\r\n	<li>(c) Verify the identification, work status, qualifications, and any other required criteria of the nanny candidate as would a prudent employer.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>INSURANCE - I/We will ensure that I/we have adequate insurance coverage for any possible losses sustained as a result of the employment of a child care worker in my/our home.</li>\r\n	<li>ADDITIONAL ADVICE MAY BE NECESSARY - While Bumble Bees offers assistance in setting up the employment relationship with any nanny candidate, I/we understand that we are ultimately responsible as employers, and will seek any such additional legal, accounting, immigration or other advice as required.</li>\r\n	<li>CONFIDENTIALITY - I/We agree to keep all information concerning nanny candidates confidential. I/We agree not to disclose any information concerning the nanny candidates provided by Bumble Bees to third parties without the express written consent of Bumble Bees. I/We acknowledge and agree that should unauthorized disclosure of such information be made to a third party resulting in the employment of a nanny candidate first introduced to me by Bumble Bees, that I may responsible to Bumble Bees for any and all fees owing.</li>\r\n	<li>LIABILITY – I/We agree that Bumble Bees will not be held liable for any claim by me/us for any loss or damage which may be incurred by us, howsoever caused, as a result of the introduction to or employment by me/us of any nanny candidate, or due the failure of Bumble Bees to introduce any nanny candidate to me/us.</li>\r\n	<li>ACCEPTANCE - By signing below I/we acknowledge having read, understood and agree to the above terms and conditions.</li>\r\n</ol>','Terms & Conditions','','inherit','open','open','','324-revision-4','','','2012-12-03 01:46:17','2012-12-03 01:46:17','',324,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/324-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(330,1,'2012-11-30 04:31:13','2012-11-30 04:31:13','<h4>Nanny, Nanny/Share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>ECE or ECA or qualified nanny qualification (you must present this at the interview)</li>\r\n	<li>At least three years full-time Professional Childcare experience if you are not ECE qualified</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Mother\'s Helper</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor</li>\r\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\r\n	<li>Willingness to learn and listen to the mother or father</li>\r\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>After School Care</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>At least one year experience working with children as a babysitter, camp counselor or studying at university (ECE, Nursing, Psychology)</li>\r\n	<li>Shows maturity and a strong interest in working with children</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to help with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Open communicator</li>\r\n	<li>At least two references associated with childcare and/or a character reference (such as Course Lecturer/Head of Education)</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Emergency Babysitter</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Studying ECE/ECA or many years childcare experience</li>\r\n	<li>CPR and First Aid certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Police check</li>\r\n	<li>Over 17 years old</li>\r\n</ul>','Requirements To Be A Bumble Bees Childcare Professional','','inherit','open','open','','205-revision-4','','','2012-11-30 04:31:13','2012-11-30 04:31:13','',205,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/205-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(331,1,'2012-12-02 00:47:41','2012-12-02 00:47:41','Sometimes sharing a nanny might be the best option for your family – a more affordable alternative!\r\n\r\nWhen two families come together to share a nanny for their children, this is called a “Nanny Share”.\r\n\r\n<strong>Option 1:</strong> The nanny can care for both sets of children on all days Monday- Friday. There is usually only 1 child from each family in this option.\r\n<strong>Option 2:</strong> The nanny alternates between caring for one family’s children on one day, and the other family’s children on the other days.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div3\"></div>\r\n\r\nWith a nanny share, the families involved should have the same philosophies on parenting, routines, discipline, etc. In most nanny shares, the involved families have one child each. Nanny share nannies usually work between 45- 50 hours per week.\r\n\r\nMany families would like to alternate between the two houses, 1-2 weeks in each home. If this is done it could unsettle the children and disrupt their routine. Consistency is very important for young children. It can also disrupt the nannies routine and schedule especially when children’s items are forgotten eg winter hats and gloves, sunscreen, bottles.\r\n\r\n<h4>Points to consider when starting a Nanny Share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>The household where the children will be based will need to have an extra sleeping area and bed (pack and play)</li>\r\n	<li>The cost of children’s groceries will need to be halved ie. milk, food, diapers, wipes</li>\r\n	<li>Transport for two children, whether it be two car seats or a double stroller if needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Transporting your child’s bottles every morning and afternoon or buying an extra set for the other house</li>\r\n	<li>For the house that is having the children that there will be more toys, bottles, plates, cups in your home.</li>\r\n	<li>When the nanny gets vacations which would work for both families. Most nannies get between 2 weeks’ vacation and the days between Christmas and New Year. For the two weeks I always recommend that the families pick one week and the nanny picks the other week to make it fair.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Positives of being a part of a Nanny share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Sharing the cost of the nanny ages/ salary</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to socialize with children their own age</li>\r\n	<li>Develop a close friendship with the other child</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to share and participate with each other.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"controls\">\r\n<button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-sharing\';\">Families With A Shared Nanny</button><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-looking\';\">Families Looking For A Shared Nanny</button>\r\n</div>','Nanny Share Family Finder','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-18','','','2012-12-02 00:47:41','2012-12-02 00:47:41','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(332,1,'2012-12-03 01:56:22','2012-12-03 01:56:22','<h4>RichelleAssenberg - Owner</h4>\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is owned and operated by RichelleAssenberg, a qualified Early Childhood Teacher and childcare professional with 12 years Early Childhood experience. Richelle started her career as a kindergarten and daycare teacher in New Zealand, before relocating to the United Kingdom to continue her work caring and nurturing children and families as a professional nanny. After settling in Toronto and consulting with several nanny agencies, Richelle knew she could offer families a more professional, customized and personal service.\r\n\r\n“Hi, my name is Richelle and I am here to help nannies and families find each other. I hope to help families find their perfect nanny efficiently and easily, while helping nannies find a family that they love working for. In my professional career, families have told me the difficulties they faced finding a trustworthy and responsible nanny, a nanny that shared their philosophy on childcare. While caring for your children, a nanny also shares your home – it’s imperative that you are able to trust and partner with your nanny in keeping your children safe and secure. My goal in operating Bumble Bees Nannies is to find that perfect relationship for family and nanny.” – <strong>RichelleAssenberg</strong> - owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n<h4>Irene MacRae</h4>','Staff at Bumble Bees Nannies','','publish','open','open','','staff-at-bumble-bees-nannies','','','2012-12-03 01:59:54','2012-12-03 01:59:54','',2,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=332',0,'page','',0),(333,1,'2012-12-03 01:56:02','2012-12-03 01:56:02','<RichelleAssenberg- Owner\n\nBumble Bees Nannies is owned and operated by RichelleAssenberg, a qualified Early Childhood Teacher and childcare professional with 12 years