tosave','','','2012-12-04 02:50:55','2012-12-04 02:50:55','',375,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/375-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(378,1,'2012-12-06 01:41:37','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-12-06 01:41:37','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=378',0,'post','',0),(379,1,'2012-12-06 01:42:56','2012-12-06 01:42:56','Quality Excellent\n\nI\'m so pleased with the experience I had with Richelle. She was in contact with me throughout the experience and she matched me with a family that matched me perfectly. I have never been happier with my work. Richelle really worked with me to find me the hours, the family, the kids and even the area that suited my wants as well as my needs. She was quick to reply to emails or phone calls which I really appreciated as I needed a job in a very short period of time and she was able to find me an appropriate family in about a month. I love working for my family and they have really welcomed me into their home. I think it\'s Richelle\'s personal touch in each placement that makes the placements work so amazingly. She really got to know me so that she could see which families I would fit with and where my skills would be best used. My family is so great I actually miss my work kids on my days off and look forward to Monday when I can go play with my girls again. I\'m so pleased with my experience and hope to be placed again when my contract ends. I recommend Bumble Bees Nannies at every chance I can Richelle is wonderful. K.W nanny in Toronto\n\n&nbsp;','Testimonials From Nannies','','inherit','open','open','','343-autosave','','','2012-12-06 01:42:56','2012-12-06 01:42:56','',343,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/343-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(380,1,'2012-12-03 02:12:52','2012-12-03 02:12:52','Quality Excellent\r\n\r\nI\'m so pleased with the experience I had with Richelle. She was in contact with me throughout the experience and she matched me with a family that matched me perfectly. I have never been happier with my work. Richelle really worked with me to find me the hours, the family, the kids and even the area that suited my wants as well as my needs. She was quick to reply to emails or phone calls which I really appreciated as I needed a job in a very short period of time and she was able to find me an appropriate family in about a month. I love working for my family and they have really welcomed me into their home. I think it\'s Richelle\'s personal touch in each placement that makes the placements work so amazingly. She really got to know me so that she could see which families I would fit with and where my skills would be best used. My family is so great I actually miss my work kids on my days off and look forward to Monday when I can go play with my girls again. I\'m so pleased with my experience and hope to be placed again when my contract ends. I recommend Bumble Bees Nannies at every chance I can Richelle is wonderful. K.W nanny in Toronto\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Testimonials From Nannies','','inherit','open','open','','343-revision-5','','','2012-12-03 02:12:52','2012-12-03 02:12:52','',343,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/343-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(381,1,'2012-11-25 04:27:24','2012-11-25 04:27:24','<div id=\"cntr-contact-info\"><strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"mailto:richelle@bbnannies.ca\">richelle@bbnannies.ca</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904</div>\r\n<div id=\"cntr-map\"></div>','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-10','','','2012-11-25 04:27:24','2012-11-25 04:27:24','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(382,1,'2012-12-06 01:44:34','2012-12-06 01:44:34','<div id=\"cntr-contact-info\"><strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n245 Carlaw Avenue Unit 307\r\nToronto Ontario\r\nM4M 2S1<a href=\"mailto:richelle@bumblebeesnannies.com\" target=\"_blank\">richelle@bumblebeesnannies.com</a>\r\n(647) 505-2904\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"cntr-map\"></div>','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-11','','','2012-12-06 01:44:34','2012-12-06 01:44:34','',55,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/55-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(383,1,'2012-12-03 02:11:58','2012-12-03 02:11:58','','Testimonials','','inherit','open','open','','349-revision-2','','','2012-12-03 02:11:58','2012-12-03 02:11:58','',349,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/349-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(384,1,'2012-12-06 01:52:58','2012-12-06 01:52:58',' ','','','publish','open','open','','384','','','2012-12-06 02:04:55','2012-12-06 02:04:55','',0,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=384',24,'nav_menu_item','',0),(385,1,'2012-12-02 02:36:06','2012-12-02 02:36:06','Here is the Job Vacancies description, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...\r\n\r\n<div class=\"controls\">\r\n<a class=\"btn\" title=\"Full Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/full-time/\">Full Time</a><a class=\"btn\" title=\"Part Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/part-time/\">Part Time</a><a class=\"btn\" title=\"After School Care\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/after-school-care/\">After School Care</a>\r\n</div>','Job Vacancies','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-10','','','2012-12-02 02:36:06','2012-12-02 02:36:06','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(386,1,'2012-12-03 02:13:48','2012-12-03 02:13:48','“After interviewing multiple nannies and not finding the right fit for our family we decided to give Bumble Bee Nannies a try. Richelle was immediately helpful and warm and took note of our special needs. All her applicants were wonderful, a step up from the other nannies we had interviewed. Ultimately, we have been extremely happy with our lovely nanny and our son definitely gives her a high five”\r\n- <strong>J.O- Mother from Leslieville</strong>\r\n\r\n“Bumble Bees Nannies were very knowledgeable and helpful when it came to finding someone for our nanny share position. Being a first-time parent, I was intimidated by the prospect of having to find a nanny to care for my son and my friend\'s daughter. Not only did they answer our many questions, but they were also able to find us a nanny that is a truly wonderful fit with both families. Our children enjoy spending time with her and we have peace of mind knowing that they are getting quality care every day. Thank you Bumble Bees Nannies!”\r\n- <strong>J.H Mother from East Toronto</strong>\r\n\r\n“Bumble Bees Nannies took the daunting task of finding the right childcare and made it simple! Richelle was such a tremendous help to my friend and I who were searching for a nanny to do a share with. We simply communicated what we were looking for and Richelle presented us with 3 women to interview and all were wonderful. We now have a fantastic nanny who is loving and interactive with our children and the kids adore her! A great service for busy parents who want the best for their family”\r\n- <strong>S.P Toronto</strong>\r\n\r\n“Great Nanny Agency! The service that we received from Richelle at Bumble Bees Nannies was unlike any other nanny agency that we have dealt with in Toronto. Previous agencies had just sent us nanny after nanny which we had to interview to find out that they were not fit with our family. Bumble Bees Nannies listened to our needs as a family and worked to find us the right nanny from the start. Richelle only had to send us 2 nannies to interview before we found the perfect match and that is all down to her hard work in the background. This saved us time and money. We have recommended using Bumble Bees Nannies to all of our friends”\r\n- <strong>Father from East Toronto</strong>','Testimonials From Parents','','inherit','open','open','','339-revision-6','','','2012-12-03 02:13:48','2012-12-03 02:13:48','',339,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/339-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(387,1,'2012-12-06 02:04:17','2012-12-06 02:04:17','<div class=\"small-type strong\">February 2004-February 2008\r\nPrivate Live-In Nanny\r\nLondon, United Kingdom</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN (28/1/08)\r\n\r\nRichelle has worked for us, for 4 years, starting in February 2004. She came to us 2 months after she had arrived from New Zealand, where during these 2 months she was temping for a family of three children. We have two children, Sebastian (Baz) and Chloe. At her time of joining us, they were 2 and half years and 7 months respectively.\r\n\r\nHaving had the same nanny since Baz was 16 weeks old,Richelle’s first priority was to spend time with our departing nanny, to ensure a ‘smooth and consistent’ hand-over of both our children’s routines. In what turned out to be a challenging situation at times, Richelle embraced this’ hand over’ with such openness, optimism and most importantly, enthusiasm, that we quickly knew we were really fortunate to have found a brilliant child carer.\r\n\r\nWithin weeks, Richelle had put her own personal stamp on the children’s routines, such as good, healthy eating, consistent sleeping patterns and most importantly, developing their social lives further.\r\n\r\nRichelle leads a very healthy lifestyle, which has impacted on Baz and Chloe. They prefer, fresh meat, fruit and vegetables to ‘fast food’ and she cooks fresh meals everyday, including a balance of meat and fish. Richelle has also introduced other nationalities into their ‘likes’ such as Chinese, Indian and Dutch delicacies!\r\n\r\nRichelle is naturally a very active, outdoor-orientated person. She has enjoyed a family gym membership, whilst with us, and through this, she has encouraged the children to get involved in weekly swimming, tennis, football and ballet lessons. Due to her own disposition, Richelle has regularly encouraged the children to try new experiences, such as skiing, boogie boarding and bungie jumping.\r\n\r\nRichelle is an extremely sociable person. She feels completely at ease talking to strangers at the children’s clubs, at the many family events we have included her in over the years and most importantly at the school gates with all the other mothers. In fact I would go as far to say that most of the mothers of my children’s friends regularly comment on what am amazing nanny Richelle is and how lucky we are – which of course we already know!\r\n\r\nNow that Baz is 6 and half years and Chloe is 4 and half years, Richelle’s priorities during term time have changed to a stronger focus on helping them with their homework. Our son is taking his prep-school entrance exams in October 2008. Richelle’s approach has been to guide them to finding the answers themselves, if she has to tell them something, she tries to focus on telling them once. This has enabled them to remember what they have learnt for themselves. As a result, my son (the youngest in his class) is now in the top stream in maths and on an accelerated reading programme. Both the Children’s teachers have complimented us on Richelle’s homework techniques\r\n\r\nAs I travel so much with my job, we were looking for someone, that was not just a nanny, but someone that would be very much part of our family. It goes without saying that Richelle is the fifth member of our family! She has accompanied us on many family holidays, both with other family friends and with the bigger Butterwick clan (grandparents, cousins etc). Richelle has got on really well with all of them, however these situations have often required her to adapt her style to accommodate other families living preferences.\r\n\r\nRichelle has been both a nanny, surrogate mother and dear friend to all of us. When our sonBaz, was 4 years old she took him to Paris on a sight-seeing trip, by themselves.\r\n\r\nI know she will continue to be very much part of our family and in the years to come we know the children will able to go and stay with her where ever her home is. If you require any further information on Richelle, please do not hesitate in contacting me.\r\n\r\nMrs Butterwick\r\nLondon\r\nW12 9QF\r\nEngland\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"small-type strong\">January 2011-July 2011\r\nNanny Share Live-Out Position\r\nToronto, Ontario</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\nJuly 20, 2011.\r\n\r\nTo whom it may concern,\r\n\r\nThis is a letter of recommendation for RichelleAssenberg, who was caregiver to our one-year-old daughter, Eve.\r\n\r\nThis was our first experience using a nanny and we can say unreservedly that Richelle far exceeded our expectations.\r\n\r\nShe proved to be thoroughly professional and capable—keeping us informed of her and the children’s activities throughout the day with emails, text messages and photos—and she employs her training in early childhood development to great effect, providing a stimulating,educational and fun environment.\r\n\r\nWhat really set her apart in our minds, however, was the extraordinary bond she formed with our daughter—a relationship that continues to this day.\r\n\r\nRichelle is a very friendly, outgoing, confident, and caring person, who has a deep and genuineaffection for the kids in her charge. It was a great comfort to us to know that Eve was being welllooked after by someone who truly loves her.\r\n\r\nWe are tremendously grateful to Richelle and happy to offer our wholehearted recommendation.\r\n\r\nFeel free to contact us at the email address below if you have any further questions\r\n\r\nMr and Mrs Jones\r\nToronto, Ontario','Richelle References','','publish','open','open','','richelle-references','','','2012-12-06 02:11:50','2012-12-06 02:11:50','',349,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=387',0,'page','',0),(388,1,'2012-12-06 02:03:27','2012-12-06 02:03:27','February 2004-February 2008 Private Live-In Nanny London, United Kingdom\nTO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN (28/1/08)\n\nRichelle has worked for us, for 4 years, starting in February 2004. She came to us 2 months after she had arrived from New Zealand, where during these 2 months she was temping for a family of three children. We have two children, Sebastian (Baz) and Chloe. At her time of joining us, they were 2 and half years and 7 months respectively.\n\nHaving had the same nanny since Baz was 16 weeks old,Richelle’s first priority was to spend time with our departing nanny, to ensure a ‘smooth and consistent’ hand-over of both our children’s routines. In what turned out to be a challenging situation at times, Richelle embraced this’ hand over’ with such openness, optimism and most importantly, enthusiasm, that we quickly knew we were really fortunate to have found a brilliant child carer.\n\nWithin weeks, Richelle had put her own personal stamp on the children’s routines, such as good, healthy eating, consistent sleeping patterns and most importantly, developing their social lives further.\n\nRichelle leads a very healthy lifestyle, which has impacted on Baz and Chloe. They prefer, fresh meat, fruit and vegetables to ‘fast food’ and she cooks fresh meals everyday, including a balance of meat and fish. Richelle has also introduced other nationalities into their ‘likes’ such as Chinese, Indian and Dutch delicacies!\n\nRichelle is naturally a very active, outdoor-orientated person. She has enjoyed a family gym membership, whilst with us, and through this, she has encouraged the children to get involved in weekly swimming, tennis, football and ballet lessons. Due to her own disposition, Richelle has regularly encouraged the children to try new experiences, such as skiing, boogie boarding and bungie jumping.\n\nRichelle is an extremely sociable person. She feels completely at ease talking to strangers at the children’s clubs, at the many family events we have included her in over the years and most importantly at the school gates with all the other mothers. In fact I would go as far to say that most of the mothers of my children’s friends regularly comment on what am amazing nanny Richelle is and how lucky we are – which of course we already know!\n\nNow that Baz is 6 and half years and Chloe is 4 and half years, Richelle’s priorities during term time have changed to a stronger focus on helping them with their homework. Our son is taking his prep-school entrance exams in October 2008. Richelle’s approach has been to guide them to finding the answers themselves, if she has to tell them something, she tries to focus on telling them once. This has enabled them to remember what they have learnt for themselves. As a result, my son (the youngest in his class) is now in the top stream in maths and on an accelerated reading programme. Both the Children’s teachers have complimented us on Richelle’s homework techniques\n\nAs I travel so much with my job, we were looking for someone, that was not just a nanny, but someone that would be very much part of our family. It goes without saying that Richelle is the fifth member of our family! She has accompanied us on many family holidays, both with other family friends and with the bigger Butterwick clan (grandparents, cousins etc). Richelle has got on really well with all of them, however these situations have often required her to adapt her style to accommodate other families living preferences.\n\nRichelle has been both a nanny, surrogate mother and dear friend to all of us. When our sonBaz, was 4 years old she took him to Paris on a sight-seeing trip, by themselves.\n\nI know she will continue to be very much part of our family and in the years to come we know the children will able to go and stay with her where ever her home is. If you require any further information on Richelle, please do not hesitate in contacting me.','Richelle References','','inherit','open','open','','387-revision','','','2012-12-06 02:03:27','2012-12-06 02:03:27','',387,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/387-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(389,1,'2012-12-06 02:04:55','2012-12-06 02:04:55',' ','','','publish','open','open','','389','','','2012-12-06 02:04:55','2012-12-06 02:04:55','',349,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=389',27,'nav_menu_item','',0),(390,1,'2012-12-06 02:04:17','2012-12-06 02:04:17','February 2004-February 2008\r\nPrivate Live-In Nanny\r\nLondon, United Kingdom\r\n\r\nTO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN (28/1/08)\r\n\r\nRichelle has worked for us, for 4 years, starting in February 2004. She came to us 2 months after she had arrived from New Zealand, where during these 2 months she was temping for a family of three children. We have two children, Sebastian (Baz) and Chloe. At her time of joining us, they were 2 and half years and 7 months respectively.\r\n\r\nHaving had the same nanny since Baz was 16 weeks old,Richelle’s first priority was to spend time with our departing nanny, to ensure a ‘smooth and consistent’ hand-over of both our children’s routines. In what turned out to be a challenging situation at times, Richelle embraced this’ hand over’ with such openness, optimism and most importantly, enthusiasm, that we quickly knew we were really fortunate to have found a brilliant child carer.\r\n\r\nWithin weeks, Richelle had put her own personal stamp on the children’s routines, such as good, healthy eating, consistent sleeping patterns and most importantly, developing their social lives further.\r\n\r\nRichelle leads a very healthy lifestyle, which has impacted on Baz and Chloe. They prefer, fresh meat, fruit and vegetables to ‘fast food’ and she cooks fresh meals everyday, including a balance of meat and fish. Richelle has also introduced other nationalities into their ‘likes’ such as Chinese, Indian and Dutch delicacies!\r\n\r\nRichelle is naturally a very active, outdoor-orientated person. She has enjoyed a family gym membership, whilst with us, and through this, she has encouraged the children to get involved in weekly swimming, tennis, football and ballet lessons. Due to her own disposition, Richelle has regularly encouraged the children to try new experiences, such as skiing, boogie boarding and bungie jumping.\r\n\r\nRichelle is an extremely sociable person. She feels completely at ease talking to strangers at the children’s clubs, at the many family events we have included her in over the years and most importantly at the school gates with all the other mothers. In fact I would go as far to say that most of the mothers of my children’s friends regularly comment on what am amazing nanny Richelle is and how lucky we are – which of course we already know!\r\n\r\nNow that Baz is 6 and half years and Chloe is 4 and half years, Richelle’s priorities during term time have changed to a stronger focus on helping them with their homework. Our son is taking his prep-school entrance exams in October 2008. Richelle’s approach has been to guide them to finding the answers themselves, if she has to tell them something, she tries to focus on telling them once. This has enabled them to remember what they have learnt for themselves. As a result, my son (the youngest in his class) is now in the top stream in maths and on an accelerated reading programme. Both the Children’s teachers have complimented us on Richelle’s homework techniques\r\n\r\nAs I travel so much with my job, we were looking for someone, that was not just a nanny, but someone that would be very much part of our family. It goes without saying that Richelle is the fifth member of our family! She has accompanied us on many family holidays, both with other family friends and with the bigger Butterwick clan (grandparents, cousins etc). Richelle has got on really well with all of them, however these situations have often required her to adapt her style to accommodate other families living preferences.\r\n\r\nRichelle has been both a nanny, surrogate mother and dear friend to all of us. When our sonBaz, was 4 years old she took him to Paris on a sight-seeing trip, by themselves.\r\n\r\nI know she will continue to be very much part of our family and in the years to come we know the children will able to go and stay with her where ever her home is. If you require any further information on Richelle, please do not hesitate in contacting me.\r\n\r\nMrs Butterwick\r\nLondon\r\nW12 9QF\r\nEngland','Richelle References','','inherit','open','open','','387-revision-2','','','2012-12-06 02:04:17','2012-12-06 02:04:17','',387,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/387-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(391,1,'2012-12-06 02:06:01','2012-12-06 02:06:01','<div class=\"small-type\">\r\nFebruary 2004-February 2008\r\nPrivate Live-In Nanny\r\nLondon, United Kingdom\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nTO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN (28/1/08)\r\n\r\nRichelle has worked for us, for 4 years, starting in February 2004. She came to us 2 months after she had arrived from New Zealand, where during these 2 months she was temping for a family of three children. We have two children, Sebastian (Baz) and Chloe. At her time of joining us, they were 2 and half years and 7 months respectively.\r\n\r\nHaving had the same nanny since Baz was 16 weeks old,Richelle’s first priority was to spend time with our departing nanny, to ensure a ‘smooth and consistent’ hand-over of both our children’s routines. In what turned out to be a challenging situation at times, Richelle embraced this’ hand over’ with such openness, optimism and most importantly, enthusiasm, that we quickly knew we were really fortunate to have found a brilliant child carer.\r\n\r\nWithin weeks, Richelle had put her own personal stamp on the children’s routines, such as good, healthy eating, consistent sleeping patterns and most importantly, developing their social lives further.\r\n\r\nRichelle leads a very healthy lifestyle, which has impacted on Baz and Chloe. They prefer, fresh meat, fruit and vegetables to ‘fast food’ and she cooks fresh meals everyday, including a balance of meat and fish. Richelle has also introduced other nationalities into their ‘likes’ such as Chinese, Indian and Dutch delicacies!\r\n\r\nRichelle is naturally a very active, outdoor-orientated person. She has enjoyed a family gym membership, whilst with us, and through this, she has encouraged the children to get involved in weekly swimming, tennis, football and ballet lessons. Due to her own disposition, Richelle has regularly encouraged the children to try new experiences, such as skiing, boogie boarding and bungie jumping.\r\n\r\nRichelle is an extremely sociable person. She feels completely at ease talking to strangers at the children’s clubs, at the many family events we have included her in over the years and most importantly at the school gates with all the other mothers. In fact I would go as far to say that most of the mothers of my children’s friends regularly comment on what am amazing nanny Richelle is and how lucky we are – which of course we already know!\r\n\r\nNow that Baz is 6 and half years and Chloe is 4 and half years, Richelle’s priorities during term time have changed to a stronger focus on helping them with their homework. Our son is taking his prep-school entrance exams in October 2008. Richelle’s approach has been to guide them to finding the answers themselves, if she has to tell them something, she tries to focus on telling them once. This has enabled them to remember what they have learnt for themselves. As a result, my son (the youngest in his class) is now in the top stream in maths and on an accelerated reading programme. Both the Children’s teachers have complimented us on Richelle’s homework techniques\r\n\r\nAs I travel so much with my job, we were looking for someone, that was not just a nanny, but someone that would be very much part of our family. It goes without saying that Richelle is the fifth member of our family! She has accompanied us on many family holidays, both with other family friends and with the bigger Butterwick clan (grandparents, cousins etc). Richelle has got on really well with all of them, however these situations have often required her to adapt her style to accommodate other families living preferences.\r\n\r\nRichelle has been both a nanny, surrogate mother and dear friend to all of us. When our sonBaz, was 4 years old she took him to Paris on a sight-seeing trip, by themselves.\r\n\r\nI know she will continue to be very much part of our family and in the years to come we know the children will able to go and stay with her where ever her home is. If you require any further information on Richelle, please do not hesitate in contacting me.\r\n\r\nMrs Butterwick\r\nLondon\r\nW12 9QF\r\nEngland','Richelle References','','inherit','open','open','','387-revision-3','','','2012-12-06 02:06:01','2012-12-06 02:06:01','',387,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/387-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(392,1,'2012-12-06 02:09:30','2012-12-06 02:09:30','<div class=\"small-type strong\">February 2004-February 2008\nPrivate Live-In Nanny\nLondon, United Kingdom</div>\n&nbsp;\n\nTO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN (28/1/08)\n\nRichelle has worked for us, for 4 years, starting in February 2004. She came to us 2 months after she had arrived from New Zealand, where during these 2 months she was temping for a family of three children. We have two children, Sebastian (Baz) and Chloe. At her time of joining us, they were 2 and half years and 7 months respectively.\n\nHaving had the same nanny since Baz was 16 weeks old,Richelle’s first priority was to spend time with our departing nanny, to ensure a ‘smooth and consistent’ hand-over of both our children’s routines. In what turned out to be a challenging situation at times, Richelle embraced this’ hand over’ with such openness, optimism and most importantly, enthusiasm, that we quickly knew we were really fortunate to have found a brilliant child carer.\n\nWithin weeks, Richelle had put her own personal stamp on the children’s routines, such as good, healthy eating, consistent sleeping patterns and most importantly, developing their social lives further.\n\nRichelle leads a very healthy lifestyle, which has impacted on Baz and Chloe. They prefer, fresh meat, fruit and vegetables to ‘fast food’ and she cooks fresh meals everyday, including a balance of meat and fish. Richelle has also introduced other nationalities into their ‘likes’ such as Chinese, Indian and Dutch delicacies!\n\nRichelle is naturally a very active, outdoor-orientated person. She has enjoyed a family gym membership, whilst with us, and through this, she has encouraged the children to get involved in weekly swimming, tennis, football and ballet lessons. Due to her own disposition, Richelle has regularly encouraged the children to try new experiences, such as skiing, boogie boarding and bungie jumping.\n\nRichelle is an extremely sociable person. She feels completely at ease talking to strangers at the children’s clubs, at the many family events we have included her in over the years and most importantly at the school gates with all the other mothers. In fact I would go as far to say that most of the mothers of my children’s friends regularly comment on what am amazing nanny Richelle is and how lucky we are – which of course we already know!\n\nNow that Baz is 6 and half years and Chloe is 4 and half years, Richelle’s priorities during term time have changed to a stronger focus on helping them with their homework. Our son is taking his prep-school entrance exams in October 2008. Richelle’s approach has been to guide them to finding the answers themselves, if she has to tell them something, she tries to focus on telling them once. This has enabled them to remember what they have learnt for themselves. As a result, my son (the youngest in his class) is now in the top stream in maths and on an accelerated reading programme. Both the Children’s teachers have complimented us on Richelle’s homework techniques\n\nAs I travel so much with my job, we were looking for someone, that was not just a nanny, but someone that would be very much part of our family. It goes without saying that Richelle is the fifth member of our family! She has accompanied us on many family holidays, both with other family friends and with the bigger Butterwick clan (grandparents, cousins etc). Richelle has got on really well with all of them, however these situations have often required her to adapt her style to accommodate other families living preferences.\n\nRichelle has been both a nanny, surrogate mother and dear friend to all of us. When our sonBaz, was 4 years old she took him to Paris on a sight-seeing trip, by themselves.\n\nI know she will continue to be very much part of our family and in the years to come we know the children will able to go and stay with her where ever her home is. If you require any further information on Richelle, please do not hesitate in contacting me.\n\nMrs Butterwick\nLondon\nW12 9QF\nEngland\n\n<hr />\n\n<div class=\"small-type strong\">\nJanuary 2011-July 2011\nNanny Share Live-Out Position\nToronto, Ontario</em></strong><strong><em>           </em></strong><strong><em></em></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nJuly 20, 2011.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTo whom it may concern,\n\nThis is a letter of recommendation for RichelleAssenberg, who was caregiver to our one-year-old daughter, Eve.\n\nThis was our first experience using a nanny and we can say unreservedly that Richelle far exceeded our expectations.\n\nShe proved to be thoroughly professional and capable—keeping us informed of her and the children’s activities throughout the day with emails, text messages and photos—and she employs her training in early childhood development to great effect, providing a stimulating,educational and fun environment.\n\nWhat really set her apart in our minds, however, was the extraordinary bond she formed with our daughter—a relationship that continues to this day.\n\nRichelle is a very friendly, outgoing, confident, and caring person, who has a deep and genuineaffection for the kids in her charge. It was a great comfort to us to know that Eve was being welllooked after by someone who truly loves her.\n\nWe are tremendously grateful to Richelle and happy to offer our wholehearted recommendation.\n\nFeel free to contact us at the email address below if you have any further questions\n\nMr and Mrs Jones\n\nToronto, Ontario','Richelle References','','inherit','open','open','','387-autosave','','','2012-12-06 02:09:30','2012-12-06 02:09:30','',387,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/387-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(393,1,'2012-12-06 02:07:29','2012-12-06 02:07:29','<div class=\"small-type strong\">February 2004-February 2008\r\nPrivate Live-In Nanny\r\nLondon, United Kingdom</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN (28/1/08)\r\n\r\nRichelle has worked for us, for 4 years, starting in February 2004. She came to us 2 months after she had arrived from New Zealand, where during these 2 months she was temping for a family of three children. We have two children, Sebastian (Baz) and Chloe. At her time of joining us, they were 2 and half years and 7 months respectively.\r\n\r\nHaving had the same nanny since Baz was 16 weeks old,Richelle’s first priority was to spend time with our departing nanny, to ensure a ‘smooth and consistent’ hand-over of both our children’s routines. In what turned out to be a challenging situation at times, Richelle embraced this’ hand over’ with such openness, optimism and most importantly, enthusiasm, that we quickly knew we were really fortunate to have found a brilliant child carer.\r\n\r\nWithin weeks, Richelle had put her own personal stamp on the children’s routines, such as good, healthy eating, consistent sleeping patterns and most importantly, developing their social lives further.\r\n\r\nRichelle leads a very healthy lifestyle, which has impacted on Baz and Chloe. They prefer, fresh meat, fruit and vegetables to ‘fast food’ and she cooks fresh meals everyday, including a balance of meat and fish. Richelle has also introduced other nationalities into their ‘likes’ such as Chinese, Indian and Dutch delicacies!\r\n\r\nRichelle is naturally a very active, outdoor-orientated person. She has enjoyed a family gym membership, whilst with us, and through this, she has encouraged the children to get involved in weekly swimming, tennis, football and ballet lessons. Due to her own disposition, Richelle has regularly encouraged the children to try new experiences, such as skiing, boogie boarding and bungie jumping.\r\n\r\nRichelle is an extremely sociable person. She feels completely at ease talking to strangers at the children’s clubs, at the many family events we have included her in over the years and most importantly at the school gates with all the other mothers. In fact I would go as far to say that most of the mothers of my children’s friends regularly comment on what am amazing nanny Richelle is and how lucky we are – which of course we already know!\r\n\r\nNow that Baz is 6 and half years and Chloe is 4 and half years, Richelle’s priorities during term time have changed to a stronger focus on helping them with their homework. Our son is taking his prep-school entrance exams in October 2008. Richelle’s approach has been to guide them to finding the answers themselves, if she has to tell them something, she tries to focus on telling them once. This has enabled them to remember what they have learnt for themselves. As a result, my son (the youngest in his class) is now in the top stream in maths and on an accelerated reading programme. Both the Children’s teachers have complimented us on Richelle’s homework techniques\r\n\r\nAs I travel so much with my job, we were looking for someone, that was not just a nanny, but someone that would be very much part of our family. It goes without saying that Richelle is the fifth member of our family! She has accompanied us on many family holidays, both with other family friends and with the bigger Butterwick clan (grandparents, cousins etc). Richelle has got on really well with all of them, however these situations have often required her to adapt her style to accommodate other families living preferences.\r\n\r\nRichelle has been both a nanny, 